1.name: Behind Neck Press
1.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return behind neck and repeat.

2.name: Front Raise
2.description: Raise barbell forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

3.name: Incline
3.description: With elbows straight or slightly bent, raise barbell up and over shoulders until uppers arm are vertical. Lower barbell to upper thigh and repeat.

4.name: Military Press
4.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower to front of neck and repeat.

5.name: Seated
5.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

6.name: Shoulder Press
6.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

7.name: Reclined
7.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

8.name: Upright Row
8.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

9.name: Wide Grip
9.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

10.name: Rear Delt Raise
10.description: Pull barbell behind hips and low back up as far as possible allowing elbows to travel up behind body to each side. Flex wrists near top of movement so bar can be raised higher. Lower until arms and wrists are straight. Repeat.

11.name: Rear Delt Row
11.description: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso, pull barbell up toward upper chest until upper arms are just beyond horizontal. Return and repeat.

12.name: Lying Rear Delt Row
12.description: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso, pull barbell up toward upper chest until upper arms are just beyond parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

13.name: Close Grip Bench Press
13.description: Lower weight to chest with elbows close to body. Push barbell back up until arms are straight. Repeat.

14.name: Incline
14.description: Lower weight to chest with elbows close to body. Push barbell up until arms are straight. Repeat.

15.name: JM Press
15.description: Lower in straight line toward neck while keeping elbows relatively high and bending them out to sides, approximately 45° from midline of body. Flex wrists slightly as bar is lowered as to keep weight of bar on base of palms. Pause when forearms mak   e solid contact with biceps. Push barbell back up until arms are straight. Repeat.

16.name: Lying Triceps Extension
16.description: Lower bar by bending elbows. As bar nears head, move elbows slightly back just enough to allow bar to clear around curvature of head. Extend arms. As bar clears head, reposition elbows to their former position until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

17.name: Decline
17.description: Lower bar by bending elbows. As bar nears head, move elbows slightly back just enough to allow bar to clear around curvature of head. Extend arms. As bar clears head, reposition elbows to its former position until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

18.name: Incline
18.description: Lower bar by bending elbows. As bar nears head, move elbows slightly back just enough to allow bar to clear around curvature of head. Extend arms. As bar clears head, reposition elbows to their former position until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

19.name: Skull Crusher
19.description: Lower bar to forehead by bending elbows. Extend arms and repeat.

20.name: Triceps Extension
20.description: Lower barbell behind upper shoulders by flexing elbows allowing forearms to travel behind upper arms with elbows remaining overhead. Raise barbell overhead by extending elbows until arms are positioned straight and vertical. Lower and repeat.

21.name: Reclined
21.description: Lower barbell behind neck by flexing elbows allowing forearms to travel behind upper arms with elbows remaining overhead. Raise barbell overhead by extending elbows until arms are positioned straight and vertical. Lower and repeat.

22.name: Curl
22.description: With elbows to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

23.name: Drag Curl
23.description: Raise barbell straight up so elbows travel back as elbows flex. Follow contour of hips and waist. As elbows continues to flex, begin bringing elbows forward when forearms rises past horizontal position. Continue upward over chest until forearms are perpendicular. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

24.name: Preacher Curl
24.description: Raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower barbell until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

25.name: Standing
25.description: Raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower barbell until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

26.name: Prone Incline Curl
26.description: Raise bar until arms are flexed. Lower barbell until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

27.name: Reverse Curl
27.description: With elbows to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

28.name: Reverse Preacher Curl
28.description: Raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower barbell until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

29.name: Standing
29.description: Raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower barbell until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

30.name: Wrist Curl
30.description: Allow barbell to roll out of palms down to fingers. Raise barbell back up by gripping and pointing knuckles up as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

31.name: Reverse Wrist Curl
31.description: Raise barbell by pointing knuckles upward as high as possible. Return until knuckles are pointing downward as far as possible. Repeat.

32.name: Bent-over Row
32.description: Pull bar to upper waist. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

33.name: Close Grip
33.description: Pull bar to waist. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

34.name: Underhand
34.description: Pull bar to waist. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

35.name: Cambered Bar Lying Row
35.description: Pull bar to upper waist or lower chest. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

36.name: Pullover
36.description: With elbows bent slightly, lower bar over and beyond head until shoulders are fully flexed or upper arms are approximately parallel to torso. Return and repeat.

37.name: Bent Arm
37.description: With elbow bent, lower bar over and just behind head until upper arm is approximately parallel to torso. Return and repeat.

38.name: Cambered Bar Seated Shrug
38.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

39.name: Shrug
39.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

40.name: Trap Bar Shrug
40.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

41.name: Elevated Stand
41.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

42.name: Bench Press
42.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

43.name: Power Lift
43.description: Lower weight to lower chest. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

44.name: Board Press
44.description: Lower weight toward lower chest on   to board. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

45.name: Floor Press
45.description: Lower weight to lower chest until the triceps are completely on the floor. Relax momentarily, then press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

46.name: Guillotine
46.description: Lower weight to neck to upper chest. Upper arms will be perpendicular to torso. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

47.name: with chains
47.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar upward until arms are extended. Repeat.

48.name: Decline Bench Press
48.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

49.name: Incline Bench Press
49.description: Lower weight to upper chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

50.name: Incline Shoulder Raise
50.description: Raise shoulders toward bar as high as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

51.name: Push Crunch
51.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench, keeping low back on bench. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

52.name: Push Sit-up
52.description: Raise torso from bench as high as possible by bending waist and hips. Keep weight positioned above shoulders. Achieve near upright posture (hip flexibility, incline, and initial hip position permitting). Return to original lying posture with back of shoulders contacting padded incline board. Repeat.

53.name: Hyperextension
53.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

54.name: Back Extension
54.description: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

55.name: Hyperextension (45°)
55.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

56.name: Back Extension (45°)
56.description: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise, or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

57.name: Bent Knee Good-morning
57.description: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

58.name: Deadlift
58.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

59.name: Block Pull
59.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

60.name: Deficit Deadlift
60.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weights to floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

61.name: Rack Pull
61.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

62.name: Sumo Deadlift
62.description: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to floor by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

63.name: Sumo Block Pull
63.description: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to blocks by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

64.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
64.description: Lower bar to top of feet by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

65.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
65.description: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips and waist. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

67.name: Trap Bar Stiff-leg Deadlift
67.description: Lower bar by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

68.name: Trap Bar Straight-leg Deadlift
68.description: With knees straight, lower bar down by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as weights approach floor. Hands should be lowered near sides of ankles. Set weight on floor. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

69.name: Bent Knee Good-morning
69.description: Keeping back straight, bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

70.name: Seated
70.description: Keeping back straight, bend torso forward as low as possible by bending hips. Raise torso until torso is upright. Repeat.

71.name: Deadlifts
71.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weights to floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

72.name: Block Pull
72.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

73.name: Deficit Deadlift
73.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weights to floor by bending hips back, while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

74.name: Rack Pull
74.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

75.name: Sumo Deadlift
75.description: Pull bar up by driving feet outward, while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to floor by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

76.name: Sumo Block Pull
76.description: Pull bar up by driving feet outward while pulling chest up. Extend knees when bar passes knees. At top of lift, when torso is upright, drive shoulders back and chest up. Return weight to blocks by bending hips back and knees pointed outward, while keeping chest high and back straight. Repeat.

77.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
77.description: With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Lower bar to top of feet by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. Repeat.

78.name: Single Leg
78.description: Lower bar to floor while raising lifted leg back behind. Keep back straight and knee of supporting leg slightly bent. Keep hip and knee of lifted leg extended throughout movement. Once stretch is felt or barbell contacts floor, return to original position by raising torso while lowering lifted leg. Straighten knee of supporting leg as torso becomes upright. Repeat.

79.name: Straight-back
79.description: With back straight, lower bar to top of feet by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight. Place weight onto floor. With knees still bent, lift bar by straightening hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

80.name: Hip Thrust
80.description: Raise bar upward by extending hips until straight. Lower and repeat.

81.name: Lunge
81.description: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

82.name: Lunge & Rear Lunge
82.description: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to original standing position.

83.name: Lunge to Rear Lunge
83.description: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to upright position. Instead of returning right foot to side of left foot, instead continue to step back with right leg while bending supporting left leg. Plant right forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting left leg until knee of rear right leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting left leg and return rear right leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

84.name: Rear Lunge
84.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

85.name: Side Lunge
85.description: Lunge to one side with first leg. Land on heel, then on forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

86.name: Walking Lunge
86.description: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

87.name: Single Leg Split Squat
87.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

88.name: Side Split Squat
88.description: Lower body toward side of angled foot by bending knee and hip of lead leg while keeping opposite leg only slightly bent. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat.

89.name: Single Leg Squat
89.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep   supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

90.name: Split Squat
90.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

92.name: Box Squat
92.description: Sit back onto box by bending hips back while bending knees, keeping shins nearly perpendicular or knees slightly behind ankles. Lower rear end back onto box in controlled manner. Rock torso back slightly. Once torso rocks forward, immediately stand back up rapidly by driving hips upward, keeping knees above ankles and chest high until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

93.name: Front Squat
93.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

94.name: Full Squat
94.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

95.name: Hack Squat
95.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Squat down by bending knees forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Repeat.

96.name: Safety Squat
96.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Repeat.

97.name: long handles
97.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand with or without assistance of arms, extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

99.name: Trap Bar Squat
99.description: Lift weight upward by extending knees and hips until straight. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weight to floor by bending hips back, while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

100.name: with chains
100.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend hips and knees until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

101.name: Zercher Squat
101.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight, hands close to body, and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are near parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

102.name: Step-up
102.description: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

103.name: Lateral
103.description: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between legs.

104.name: Trap Bar Deadlift
104.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weight to floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

105.name: Stiff-leg
105.description: Lower bar by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. With knees bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

106.name: Straight-back
106.description: With back straight, lower bar toward floor by bending at hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight. Place weight onto floor. With knees still bent, lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

107.name: Lunge
107.description: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

108.name: Lunge & Rear Lunge
108.description: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to original standing position.

109.name: Lunge to Rear Lunge
109.description: Lunge forward with right leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of right front leg until knee of rear left leg is almost in contact with floor. Forcibly extending hip and knee of forward right leg to return to upright position. Instead of returning right foot to side of left foot, instead continue to step back with right leg while bending supporting left leg. Plant right forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting left leg until knee of rear right leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting left leg and return rear right leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

110.name: Rear Lunge
110.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

111.name: Side Lunge
111.description: Lunge to one side with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

112.name: Walking Lunge
112.description: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

113.name: Single Leg Split Squat
113.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

114.name: Side Split Squat
114.description: Lower body toward side of angled foot by bending knee and hip of lead leg while keeping opposite leg only slightly bent. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat.

115.name: Single Leg Squat
115.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep   supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

116.name: Split Squat
116.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

117.name: Squat
117.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

119.name: Full Squat
119.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

120.name: Hack Squat
120.description: Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Repeat.

121.name: Safety Squat
121.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Repeat.

122.name: long handles
122.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand with or without assistance of arms, extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

124.name: Trap Bar Squat
124.description: Lift weight upward by extending knees and hips until straight. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weights to floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward. Repeat.

125.name: with chains
125.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

126.name: Zercher Squat
126.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight, hands close to body, and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are near parallel. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

127.name: Step-up
127.description: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

128.name: Lateral
128.description: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side slightly forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg alternating between legs.

129.name: Good-morning
129.description: Keeping back straight, bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

130.name: Glute-Ham Raise
130.description: From lower position, raise torso by extending hips until fully extended. Continue to raise body by flexing knees until body is upright. Lower body by straightening knees until body is horizontal. Continue to lower torso by bending hips until body is upside down. Repeat.

131.name: Inverse Leg Curl
131.description: Lower body until horizontal by straightening knees. Raise body by flexing knees only allowing hips to bend slightly. Repeat.

132.name: Hyperextension
132.description: Raise upper body until hip and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until fully flexed. Repeat.

133.name: Back Raise
133.description: Lower body by bending hips until fully flexed. Raise, or extend hips until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

134.name: Hyperextension (45°)
134.description: Raise upper body until hip and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until fully flexed. Repeat.

135.name: Back Raise (45°)
135.description: Lower body by bending hips until fully flexed. Raise or extend hips until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

136.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
136.description: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as bar approaches top of feet. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

137.name: Straight-back
137.description: With knees and back straight, lower bar by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Lift bar by extending hips until upright. Pull shoulders slightly back at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

138.name: Trap Bar Straight-leg Deadlift
138.description: With knees straight, lower bar down by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as weights approach foor. Hands should be lowered near sides of ankles. Set weight on floor. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

139.name: Straight-back
139.description: With knees and back straight, lower bar by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Lift bar by extending hips until upright. Pull shoulders slightly back at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

140.name: Safety Calf Raise
140.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

141.name: Standing Calf Raise
141.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

142.name: Safety Barbell Seated Calf Raise
142.description: Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Repeat.

143.name: Reverse Calf Raise
143.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

144.name: Safety Bar Reverse Calf Raise
144.description: Pull forefeet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

148.name: Shoulders Stretch
148.description:
Reach one arm behind your body, with your elbow pointing upward behind your head.
Assist the stretch with your other hand on your elbow to engage your shoulder.
Pause for a few seconds, then repeat the stretch with your other arm.

149.name: Shoulders Stretch
149.description:
Start with your arms at either side. Begin by pushing your shoulders forward and in towards your chest.
Repeat as necessary.
Continue the circular motion with your shoulders, pinching up towards your ears, and then extending your chest outwards while you finish the motion.

150.name: Shoulders Stretch
150.description:
Place the top of your hand into the small of your back, your arm at a 90° angle.
Hold your elbow with the other arm, and slowly pull the arm forward until you feel your shoulder engaged in the stretch. Pause at the apex of the stretch and return to the starting position.
Return to starting position, and repeat with your other arm.

151.name: Shoulders Stretch
151.description:
Stand with you feet shoulder width apart. Place one arm across the front of your chest at shoulder height, press the forearm of your other arm above the elbow, hooking the stretching arm with your hand.
Press the arm until it is straight and rotate your upper torso to engage the stretch even deeper.
Repeat with your other arm.

155.name: Forearms Stretch
155.description:
Place your palm flush against the wall.
Take one step forward and straighten your arm slowly to extend your bicep.
Hold at the peak of the stretch.
Return to starting position.

156.name: Forearms Stretch
156.description:
Place your hand against a wall, palms facing upward, with finger tips touching.
Hold at the peak of the stretch.
Return to starting position.
Slowly lean into your palm.

157.name: Forearms Stretch
157.description:
Place your hands together.
Rotate your arms and hands 180°.
Hold at the peak of the stretch.
Return to starting position.

158.name: Forearms Stretch
158.description:
Raise your arm to shoulder height at 90° to your body.
Press lightly on your hand and push towards you.
Rotate the arm across your body.
Switch sides and repeat.

160.name: Lever
160.description: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm position.

164.name: Lever
164.description: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch.

168.name: Supine Lat
168.description: Pull arms toward floor and back sides of head. Hold stretch.

171.name: Upper Trapezius
171.description: Tilt head away from lowered shoulder by positioning ear toward front of opposite shoulder. Hold stretch. Repeat to other side.

172.name: Chair Trapezius
172.description: Pull up on chair leg by position torso more upright while allowing left shoulder to be pulled downward. Hold stretch. Repeat on opposite side while sitting slightly angled to left.

175.name: Broomstick
175.description: Pull upper end of pole forward so shoulder is internally rotated. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

180.name: Supine Infraspinatus
180.description: Keeping elbows bend at a right angles, push forearms downward toward floor and hold stretch.

181.name: Prone Infraspinatus
181.description: Lower bend arms toward floor and hold stretch.

182.name: Broomstick
182.description: Pull lower end of pole forward and upward so shoulder is externally rotated. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite arm.

184.name: Chest Stretch
184.description:
Using a raised wall, place your arm at a 90° angle against it.
With a staggered stance, lean into the wall extending your chest.
Pause for a few seconds and then return to starting position and repeat on opposite side.

185.name: Chest Stretch
185.description:
Lay on your side with one hand just in front of you.
With a slight bend in your arm, rotate your arm around your body as slowly as possible.
Return to the starting position and then repeat on the other side.

186.name: Chest Stretch
186.description:
Place your arms behind your back and clasp your hands together.
Slowly extend your elbows until they are locked then lift them away from you.
Pause in this position for a few seconds and then return them to starting position.

187.name: Chest Stretch
187.description:
Raise your arms to shoulder height, fully extended in front of you.
Slowly bring your arms behind your back still at shoulder height.
Pause for a few seconds and then return to starting position.

197.name: Movement
197.description: Flex spine by hunching back up. Extend spine by arching back. Repeat.

199.name: Lever
199.description: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch.

205.name: Lever
205.description: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

217.name: Standing
217.description: Lean down, lowering torso toward thighs. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

233.name: Lever
233.description: Squat down with back straight while straightening hip of rear leg by pushing hips forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

235.name: On Bench
235.description: Slowly lunge forward by continuing to bend forward leg. With chest high, straighten hip of rear leg by driving hips down and forward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

245.name: Lever
245.description: Push and lower seat back. Repeat with opposite leg.

257.name: Seated
257.description: Pull ankle or forefoot to rear end and straighten hip by moving knee backwards. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

258.name: Standing
258.description: Pull ankle or forefoot to rear end and straighten hip by moving knee backward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

259.name: Towel
259.description: Pull foot to rear end with towel and straighten hip by moving knee backward. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

260.name: Apparatus
260.description: Bend supporting knee slightly while positioning hip back closer to heel. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

261.name: Platform
261.description: Bend supporting knee while positioning hip back closer to heel. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite side.

262.name: Seated
262.description: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg.

267.name: Vertical
267.description: Straighten elevated knee until slight stretch is felt in back of thigh. If no stretch is felt, slowly straighten bent leg until slight stretch is felt in back of thigh. Hold stretch. Repeat with opposite leg on opposite side of wall or column.

280.name: Lever
280.description: Push and lower seat back. Hold stretch.

283.name: Towel
283.description: Lower bonded leg out to side while controlling its descent and position with arm. Hold stretch. Repeat on opposite side.

299.name: Calves Stretch
299.description:
Place the ball of your foot against the wall with your heel on the ground. Place your hands on the wall in front of your shoulders.
Keeping your knee straight, slowly lean towards the wall, pause for a few seconds when you feel the stretch extending through your calf muscle.
Return to the starting position, and repeat the stretch with your other leg.

300.name: Calves Stretch
300.description:
With both feet flat on the ground, place one leg in front of your shoulder, your other leg should mirror this position behind your other shoulder. In the starting position both of your knees should be straight.
Place the palms of your hands against the wall at shoulder height in front of you, lean towards the wall and bend your front leg at the knee while keeping your back leg straight.
Pause at the apex of the stretch and return to the starting position. Switch the position of your legs and repeat.

301.name: Calves Stretch
301.description:
Balance the balls of your feet on the platform, leaning forward to use the wall to assist with balance. Engage your calves so that your feet are flat before beginning the stretch.
Lower the heels of your feet towards the ground and pause, then push through the balls of your feet like you are standing tip toe, pausing at the apex of the stretch.
Repeat as necessary.

302.name: Traps Stretch
302.description:
Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Place your left hand on your head and gently pull your head down towards your left shoulder. Then return to centre point.
Repeat, using your right hand pulling towards your right shoulder.

303.name: Traps Stretch
303.description:
Keeping your chest facing forward, turn your head 90 degrees to the left. Then return to centre point.
Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Repeat, turning your head in the other direction.

304.name: Traps Stretch
304.description:
Stand upright with your feet shoulder width apart.
Nod your head forward, bringing your chin to your chest.
You will feel the stretch across your neck.

305.name: Biceps Stretch
305.description:
Stand one foot in front of the other with the wall to your right, an arms width away.
Place your hand on the wall, fingers pointing away from you.
Gently lean forward, keeping your hand stationary.
Repeat with the other arm.

306.name: Biceps Stretch
306.description:
Stand facing the wall, an arm's width away.
Place your hand on the wall with your fingers pointing down.
Lean slightly into the wall to feel the stretch in your bicep.

307.name: Biceps Stretch
307.description:
Bend your arm at the elbow, raising your hand to your shoulder.
Using your other hand, stretch the arm down to its full extent.

308.name: Biceps Stretch
308.description:
Stand an arms width away from the wall.
Raise your arms out behind you, and place them on the wall with your fingers pointing up.
Bend your knees whilst keeping your hands in the same position.

309.name: Abdominals Stretch
309.description:
Lay on your stomach on the floor with your forearms flat on the ground.
Extend your elbows and push your upper body upwards.
Push your upper body upwards until you feel a stretch in your abs, then return to the starting position and repeat.

310.name: Abdominals Stretch
310.description:
Stand upright.
Reach with both hands upwards until you can interlock your fingers.
With your hands above your head, lean back until a stretch is felt in the abdominals.

311.name: Abdominals Stretch
311.description:
Reach up with your left arm and then lean slowly to the right. Lean until a stretch is felt in the obliques.
Stand upright.
After completing the desired amount of reps with the left arm, switch to the right arm and lean to the left.

312.name: Abdominals Stretch
312.description:
Lay on a ball or a Bosu ball with your feet firmly planted on the floor.
Lean all the way back until you feel a stretch in your abdomen.
Crunch upwards and hold for a 1-2 count.
Slowly return to the starting position and repeat.

313.name: Quads Stretch
313.description:
Stand perpendicular to a wall, using one arm against the wall for balance. With your other arm, grab the top of your foot.
Pull your leg upwards and back to engage your quads, pausing at the apex of the stretch for a few seconds.
Return to starting position and repeat with your other leg.

314.name: Quads Stretch
314.description:
Place one foot flat on the ground in front of you at a 90° angle. With your other leg, balance upon your knee, placing the tip of your foot against the wall behind you for balance.
Place your hands on your knee in front of you, and lean forward so that your knee extends over your foot.
Pause at the apex of the stretch, and slowly return to starting position. Repeat with your other leg.

315.name: Quads Stretch
315.description:
Lay flat on your belly, with both hands reach back and grab the tops of your feet.
Keeping your upper legs flat on the ground, pull both of your feet towards your buttocks.
Pause at the apex of the stretch, then return to starting position.

316.name: Quads Stretch
316.description:
Lay flat on your belly. Extend one arm out in front of you, placing your palm on the floor. With your other arm, grab the top of your foot.
Keeping your upper leg flat on the floor, pull your foot towards your buttocks to engage the stretch.
Pause for a few seconds, and then repeat the stretch with your other leg.

317.name: Traps (mid-back) Stretch
317.description:
Repeat with your other arm.
Stand up with your feet shoulder width apart. Place one arm across the front of your chest at shoulder height, press the forearm of your other arm above the elbow, hooking the stretching arm with your hand.
Press the arm until it is straight and rotate your upper torso to engage the stretch even deeper.

318.name: Traps (mid-back) Stretch
318.description:
Sit on the ground and lay one leg flat and the other over the top.
Hold your leg with the same side arm and slowly rotate your hips and back.
Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Switch sides and repeat.

319.name: Triceps Stretch
319.description:
Use the opposite hand to gently apply pressure to the elbow.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then repeat with the other arm.
Raise your left arm above your head, and bend at the elbow so your hand is resting at the top of your back.

320.name: Triceps Stretch
320.description:
Hold a band so it is in line with your spine. Hold the top with your right hand and the bottom with your left.
Keeping the top still, pull down on the band.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then repeat with the other arm.

321.name: Triceps Stretch
321.description:
Bend your left arm so your hand is at your shoulder, and hold your elbow with the opposite hand.
Gently push on your elbow so it is raised by your head.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then repeat with the other arm.

322.name: Lats Stretch
322.description:
Place both hands on the wall in front of you.
Slowly lower your body until you feel the stretch.
Hold at the bottom of the stretch, return to starting position.

323.name: Lats Stretch
323.description:
Stand up right and raise your hand to a full stretch above your head.
Slowly lean across your body and trace the opposite hand down your leg.
Hold at the bottom of the stretch, return to starting position and then switch sides.

324.name: Lats Stretch
324.description:
Find a wall to lean against, lay your tricep against the wall with your hand behind your back.
Slowly lean into the wall.
Return to starting position, then switch sides.

325.name: Lower back Stretch
325.description:
Sit on the floor with the tops of your feet pointed and flat on the ground. Move your arms out in front of you in the diving position, placing your palms flat against the ground.
With your arms fully extended, rest your buttocks on the heels of your feet, you can crawl your hands forward to extend the stretch if need be.
Hold the extended position for a few seconds, and return to starting position.

326.name: Lower back Stretch
326.description:
Lay flat on the floor with your arms at either side.
With one leg, hook one foot under the joint of your other leg.
Rotate your hips so that your knees are pointing sideways, keeping your hooked leg flat against the floor.
Pause at the apex of the stretch and repeat with your other leg.

327.name: Lower back Stretch
327.description:
Lay on your back with your arms at either side.
Raise your knees so that they are pointing straight towards the ceiling. Keeping your legs pressed together, rotate your hips to either side.
Repeat this motion as necessary.

328.name: Lower back Stretch
328.description:
Lay flat against the ground with your knees at an angle and your feet flat against the floor.
Grab your legs just below the knees, and pull your legs towards your chest.
Pause at the apex of the stretch, then return to the starting position.

329.name: Glutes Stretch
329.description:
On your front, place one leg forward and then stretch out the same side arm across the mat/floor.
Fully extend your leg and arm.
Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Switch sides and repeat.

330.name: Glutes Stretch
330.description:
Sit on the ground and lay one leg flat and the other over the top.
Hold your leg with the same side arm and slowly rotate your hips and back.
Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Switch sides and repeat.

331.name: Glutes Stretch
331.description:
Lay flat and bring your left leg to 90°.
Hold your left leg with both hands and slowly rotate your hips to the right hand side.
Hold at the peak of the stretch, then slowly return to starting position.
Switch sides and repeat.

332.name: Hamstrings Stretch
332.description:
Lie down with your legs reaching up the wall. your bum should be slightly off the floor.
Bend one leg and leave the other outstretched.
Push your thigh towards the wall.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then return to starting position.

333.name: Hamstrings Stretch
333.description:
Bend your rear leg as much as you can, keeping the front leg straight.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then return to starting position.
Stand with one foot in front of the other.

334.name: Hamstrings Stretch
334.description:
Sit on the floor with one leg outstretched and the other bent at the knee, foot resting on the opposite inner thigh.
Reach forward to touch the toes of the outstretched leg.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then return to starting position.

335.name: Hamstrings Stretch
335.description:
Sit on the floor with your legs out in front of you.
Reach forward to try and touch your toes. Reach as far forward as you can go.
Hold the stretch for a few seconds then return to starting position.

336.name: Incline Shrug
336.description:
Leaning across the back section of the bench, with feet firmly on the floor and with arms hanging to the sides.
Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.

337.name: Kettlebell Silverback Shrug
337.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.

338.name: Upright Row
338.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

339.name: Shrug
339.description:
Standing up straight with feet shoulder width apart.
Holding the kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together.
Release the shrug and repeat

340.name: Single Arm Rear Delt Fly
340.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Bring one arm behind you and rest this arm on your back. With the other arm, hold the kettlebell at arm’s length close to the floor.
Swing the kettlebell out and up towards the side of your body and then return to centre. Repeat.

341.name: Front Raise
341.description:
Stand up straight with feet shoulder width apart, holding the kettlebell in front of your pelvis.
Keeping arms straight, raise the kettlebell slightly higher than head level.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

342.name: Rear Delt Row
342.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your upper chest and then lower the kettlebell- repeat.

343.name: Long Lever Lateral Raise
343.description:
Stand with feet shoulder width apart holding a kettlebell with one hand at your side.
Keeping your arm straight, swing the kettlebell up and out, away from your body to around head height, holding on to the kettlebell firmly so it doesn’t change position in your hand.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

344.name: Chest Press
344.description:
Laying on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, hold the kettlebell at your chest with both hands.
Fully extend your arms, raising the kettlebell until your elbows are locked.
Lower the kettlebell to the starting position and repeat.

345.name: Single Arm Press
345.description:
Laying on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, leave one arm resting to the side of the body.
Using the other arm, hold the kettlebell at arms length directly upwards of your shoulder.
Lower your arm until your upper arm to elbow is resting on the floor.
Return to starting position.

346.name: Single Arm Chest Fly
346.description:
Lie on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, with your arms to the side of your body.
Holding a kettlebell in one hand, keeping your arm fully extended with a slight bend in the elbow and your forearms facing upwards, lift the kettlebell above your chest.
Lower the kettlebell to the starting position and repeat.

347.name: Walkover Pushup
347.description:
Starting in a press up position with feet wide and one hand resting on the kettlebell, complete a full press up, lowering your chest towards the ground while keeping your body straight and returning to the starting position.
Swap hands on the kettlebell, placing the hand originally on the kettlebell underneath your shoulder, complete another press up.
Repeat.

348.name: Goblet Curl
348.description:
Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis.
Raise the kettlebell bending your arms at the elbow until the kettlebell is level with your chest.
Lower to the starting position and repeat.

349.name: Single Arm Curl
349.description:
Stand up straight with a kettlebell in one hand with your forearm facing out.
Raise the kettlebell, bending your arm at the elbow and keeping your forearm vertical until your palm faces the shoulder.
Lower to the starting position and repeat.

350.name: Preacher Curl
350.description:
Stand behind a bench, with your chest leaning over the edge of the bench.
With one arm resting on the bench, hold the kettlebell, bending the arm at the elbow.
Lower your arm using the bench as a guide, keeping your forearm straight.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

351.name: Concentration Curl
351.description:
Sitting on a chair with your legs apart, rest your arm against your thigh and hold the kettlebell with your arm extended towards the floor.
Bending your arm at the elbow, lift the kettlebell until your palm faces your shoulder.
Lower to the starting position and repeat.

352.name: Wrist Curl
352.description:
Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, with your forearms facing outwards.
Flex your wrist towards your body until the kettlebell is level with your stomach.
Lower to the starting position and repeat.

353.name: Wrist Extension
353.description:
Stand up straight with a kettlebell in both hands in front of your pelvis, with your forearms facing inwards.
Flex your wrist upwards until wrists are fully extended.
Lower to the starting position and repeat.

354.name: Farmer’s Carry
354.description:
Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, lift the knee of one leg off the floor to knee height.
Bring the leg back to standing and repeat with the other leg, keeping the kettlebell on the same side.
Repeat.

355.name: Windmill
355.description:
Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart. Hold the kettlebell in one hand and extend your arm above your head.
Keeping your legs straight and the kettlebell above your head, lower the relaxed arm towards the ground, twisting your body towards the side of the raised arm.
Return to the starting potion, tilt your pelvis forward and repeat.

356.name: Situp
356.description:
Lay flat on your back with straight legs and hold the kettle bell above your chest at arm’s length.
Draw your belly into the base of your spine to engage the muscles, then raise your head and shoulders off the floor with the kettlebell raised at arm’s length above your chest.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

357.name: Woodchopper
357.description:
Stand with feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart and hold the kettle bell with both hands against your hip.
Keeping your arms straight, swing the kettlebell upwards and across your body towards your shoulder, raising the kettlebell to head height rotating your hips as you do so.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

358.name: Russian Twist
358.description:
Sit on the floor with your legs bent, knees together and feet raised slightly off the floor.
Starting on one side and sitting up straight with your core muscles engaged, lift the kettlebell off the floor with both hands and bring it across your body to the other side, rotating your chest towards the floor as you do so.
Tap the kettlebell lightly on the floor and bring the kettlebell back across your body to the starting position, rotating your chest towards the floor.
Repeat, keeping the legs bent and feet raised throughout the exercise.

359.name: Forward Lunge
359.description:
Stand straight with your feet slightly apart and hold a kettlebell in one hand.
Bring the same leg as the arm holding the kettlebell in front of you, squat down until your thigh is parallel to the ground, keeping your back straight.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

360.name: Step Up
360.description:
Standing up straight, using a bench as a step, raise one foot onto the bench and hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the straight leg.
Stand and bring both feet onto the bench. Slowly lower your leg back down to the starting position.
Repeat.

361.name: Goblet Squat
361.description:
Hold the weight tucked into your upper chest area, keeping your elbows in. Your feet should be slightly wider than your shoulders.
Sink down into the squat, keeping your elbows inside the track of your knees.
Push through your heels while keeping your chest up and return to the starting position.

362.name: Lateral Lunge
362.description:
Stand straight with your feet shoulder width apart. Keep your back straight and hold the kettlebell in front of your pelvis.
Take a large step to one side, holding the kettlebell low and lunge into the bent leg.
Return to the starting position and repeat

363.name: Calf Raise
363.description:
Standing straight with a kettlebell in each hand, raise your heels upwards while keeping your knees stationary.
Pause when your heels are fully extended and then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.

364.name: Single Leg Calf Raise
364.description:
Standing straight with a kettlebell in one hand, lift the same foot as the side without the kettlebell off the floor.
Raise your heel upwards while keeping your knees stationary.
Pause when your heels are fully extended and then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.

365.name: Seated Calf Raise
365.description:
Sitting comfortably on a chair with your core stomach muscles engaged, place your feet on the floor.
Place the kettlebell on your legs, just above the knees and raise your heels upwards off the floor.
Pause when your heels are fully extended and then slowly return to the starting position and repeat.

366.name: Incline Shrug
366.description:
Leaning across the back section of the bench, with feet firmly on the floor and with arms hanging to the sides.
Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.

367.name: Kettlebell Silverback Shrug
367.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Holding the kettlebell in both hands engage your shoulder blades, as if you are trying to touch them together. Release the shrug.

368.name: Row
368.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

369.name: Deadlift
369.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Return to standing position and repeat.

370.name: Tate Press
370.description:
Lie flat on your back. Keeping your arm straight, hold the kettlebell above your chest with your palm facing away from your body.
Bend your arm, touching the kettlebell to the top of the shoulder opposite to the arm being worked.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

371.name: Decline Skull Crusher
371.description:
Lie on the floor with your upper back and soles of feet on the floor, knees bent, and pelvis and lower back suspended in the air.
Hold the kettlebell in both hands directly above your chest.
Keeping your upper arms in place, bend your elbows to bring the kettlebell to the floor above your head.
Return the kettlebell to the starting position and repeat.

372.name: Standing Tricep Extension
372.description:
Stand with legs shoulder width apart.
Hold the kettlebell in both hands behind your head.
Straighten arms bringing kettlebell above your head.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

373.name: Skull Crusher
373.description:
Lie on your back with knees in the air and soles of your feet flat on the floor.
Hold the kettlebell in both hands directly above your chest.
Keeping your upper arms in place, bend your elbows to slowly bring the kettlebell in front of your forehead.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

374.name: Row
374.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

375.name: Single Arm Row
375.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same hand as the leg shifted backwards.
Bend forwards at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knee, keeping your back straight.
Lift the kettlebell upwards towards your chest and lower - repeat.

376.name: Pullover
376.description:
Rest your upper back on the bench and place soles of your feet firmly on the floor keeping torso and thighs suspended and parallel to the floor.
Hold the kettlebell with both hands above your chest, keeping your arms straight.
Keeping your arms straight, move the kettlebell in the direction of your head until your arms are parallel to the floor.
Return to starting to position and repeat.

377.name: Shoulder Extension
377.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart bending forward at the hips as far as comfortable. Place off-hand on the same side thigh for stability.
Hold the kettlebell in one hand, straight armed and pointing towards the floor.
Keeping your arm straight, swing the kettlebell behind you as far as comfortable.
Return to the starting position and repeat.

378.name: Staggered Deadlift
378.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees and keep your back straight.
Return to the upright position and repeat.

379.name: Kettlebell Swing
379.description:
Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell between your legs, with your knees slightly bent.
Keeping your back straight, swing the kettlebell upwards until the kettlebell is level with your chest and carefully lower.
Repeat

380.name: Goblet Good Morning
380.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your chest.
Bend forward at the hips keeping your back and knees straight and the kettlebell close to your chest.
Return to standing position and thrust your pelvis forward.

381.name: Deadlift
381.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Return to standing position and repeat.

382.name: Hip Thrust
382.description:
Sitting on the floor with your knees bent and feet planted firmly on the floor, lean your back against the bench.
Resting the kettlebell on your pelvis, raise your pelvis until your stomach, pelvis and thighs are in line.
Slowly lower until you are in the starting position and repeat.

383.name: Glute Bridge
383.description:
Laying on the floor with your knees bent and feet firmly on the floor, rest the kettlebell on your pelvis.
Pushing through the legs and keeping the core muscles engaged, raise your pelvis off the floor until your stomach, pelvis and thighs make a straight line.
Slowly lower to the ground to the starting position and repeat.

384.name: Single Leg Glute Bridge
384.description:
Laying on the floor with one knee bent with the foot firmly on the floor and one leg extended, rest the kettlebell on your pelvis.
Pushing through the bent leg and keeping the core muscles engaged, raise your pelvis and the extended leg off the floor until your stomach, pelvis and thighs make a straight line.
Slowly lower to the ground to the starting position and repeat.

385.name: Single Leg Hip Thrust
385.description:
Sitting on the floor with one knee bent with the foot firmly on the floor and one leg extended, lean your back against the bench.
Resting the kettlebell on your pelvis, raise your pelvis until your stomach, pelvis and thighs are in line.
Slowly lower until you are in the starting position and repeat.

386.name: Staggered Deadlift
386.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, shifting one foot behind you. Hold the kettlebell in both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees and keep your back straight.
Return to the upright position and repeat.

387.name: Kettlebell Swing
387.description:
Stand with your feet slightly wider than shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell between your legs, with your knees slightly bent.
Keeping your back straight, swing the kettlebell upwards until the kettlebell is level with your chest and carefully lower.
Repeat

388.name: Single Leg Deadlift
388.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart, lifting one foot off the floor behind you. Hold the kettlebell in the same arm as the lifted leg.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you extend your lifted leg behind you, keeping your back straight - holding out your arm to the side for balance.
Return to the upright position and repeat.

389.name: Deadlift
389.description:
Stand with your feet shoulder width apart holding the kettlebell with both hands in front of your thighs.
Bend forward at the hips bringing the kettlebell to the floor while you slightly bend your knees, keeping your back straight.
Return to standing position and repeat.

390.name: Front Neck Bridge
390.description: Roll back onto forehead until nose touches mat. Roll forward onto top of head until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

391.name: Wall Front Neck Bridge
391.description: Roll down onto forehead until nose touches mat. Roll up onto top of head until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

392.name: Wall Side Neck Bridge
392.description: Push side of head into mat and roll onto top of head moving body away from mat. Return to original position by rolling back down to side of head while bringing shoulder back over end of column or wall. Repeat.

393.name: Rear Neck Bridge
393.description: Extend hips and knees while pushing head back into floor. Roll back on head while arching spine high off of floor. Hyperextend neck back in attempt to bring forehead toward mat. Return body to close to mat until back of head and shoulders make contact with mat. Repeat.

394.name: Wall Rear Neck Bridge
394.description: Push head back into mat and roll head upward. Arch spine and straighten knees. Hyperextend neck so head is facing up. Return to origianl position by rolling head down while allowing low back to straighten and knees to bend slightly. Continue down until back of head and shoulders make contact with mat. Repeat.

395.name: Handstand Push-up
395.description: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

396.name: on parallettes
396.description: While maintaining body balanced over bars, push inverted body up by extending arms until straight. Lower body down by bending arms until shoulders are close to bars. Repeat.

397.name: Pike Press
397.description: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

398.name: Elevated
398.description: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

399.name: Inverted Row
399.description: Lower body downward until arms are extended straight while keeping body straight and elbows high (upper arm perpendicular to torso). Pull body toward bar until upper arms are just beyond parallel to one another. Return and repeat.

400.name: high bar
400.description: Lower body back until arms are extended straight while keeping body straight and elbows high (upper arm perpendicular to torso). Pull body toward bar until upper arms are just beyond parallel to one another. Return and repeat.

401.name: on hips
401.description: Keeping hips on floor, low back straight, and elbow pointed out to sides; pull torso up to bar. Return when upper arms are just beyond parallel to one another. Lower body downward until arms are extended straight. Return and repeat.

402.name: Bench Dip
402.description: Lower body by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder, or rear end touches floor. Raise body and repeat.

403.name: knees bent
403.description: Lower body by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder, or rear end touches floor. Raise body and repeat.

404.name: heel on floor
404.description: Lower body by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder, or rear end touches floor. Raise body and repeat.

405.name: Close Grip Push-up
405.description: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

406.name: Decline
406.description: Keeping body straight, lower upper body to floor by bending arms. To allow for full descent, pull head back slightly without arching back. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

407.name: on knees
407.description: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

408.name: on medicine ball
408.description: Keeping body straight, lower body by bending arms until chest touches ball. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

409.name: Incline on bar
409.description: Keeping body straight, lower chest to bar by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

410.name: Suspended Triceps Extension
410.description: Keeping body straight, raise body up and back up until arms are extended. Lower body by bending elbows, allowing head to travel between ends of rope. Repeat.

411.name: Triceps Dip
411.description: Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

412.name: between benches
412.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to point back. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

413.name: bent knees
413.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to point back. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

414.name: Chin-up
414.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

415.name: Underhand Inverted Row
415.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

416.name: High Bar
416.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

422.name: Inverted Row
422.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

423.name: Feet Elevated
423.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

424.name: High Bar
424.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

425.name: On Hips
425.description: Keeping hips on floor and low back straight, pull torso up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

426.name: Underhand Inverted Row
426.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

427.name: High Bar
427.description: Keeping body straight, pull body up to bar. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

428.name: Chin-up
428.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

429.name: Neutral Grip
429.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

430.name: Parallel Close Grip Pull-up
430.description: Pull body up until elbow are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

431.name: Pull-up
431.description: Pull body up until chin is above bar. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

432.name: Neutral Grip
432.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

433.name: open-centered bar
433.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

434.name: Rear Pull-up
434.description: Pull body up until bar touches back of neck. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

435.name: Stability Ball Rollout
435.description: Lean forward and roll ridged arms out over ball. Roll forward as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until kneeling upright in original position. Repeat.

436.name: Wheel Rollout
436.description: With arms straight, roll wheel out as far as possible. Lower body gently to floor extending arms forward. Raise body back up by flexing hips and pulling arms back to original position. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

437.name: Inverted Shrug
437.description: Raise body up a high as possible by pulling shoulders toward ears. Lower body to original position and repeat.

438.name: Chest Dip
438.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

439.name: between benches
439.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

440.name: bent knees
440.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

441.name: Push-up
441.description: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

442.name: Incline
442.description: Keeping body straight, lower chest to edge of box or platform by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

443.name: on bar
443.description: Keeping body straight, lower chest to bar by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

444.name: on knees
444.description: Keeping body straight and knees bent, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

445.name: Decline Push-up
445.description: Keeping body straight, lower upper body to floor by bending arms. To allow for full descent, pull head back slightly without arching back. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

446.name: on stability ball
446.description: Keeping hips straight, lower upper body to floor by bending arms. To allow for full descent, pull head back slightly without arching back. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

447.name: Pike Push-up
447.description: Lower head between ends of benches by bending arms. Push body back up to original position by extending arms. Repeat.

448.name: Push-up Plus
448.description: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Continue lifting body further up by pushing shoulders infront of chest. Repeat.

449.name: Back Extension on ball
449.description: Raise torso off of ball by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex. Repeat.

450.name: arms crossed
450.description: Raise torso off of ball by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex. Repeat.

451.name: arms up
451.description: Raise torso off of ball and hands over head by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex with arms being lowered toward floor. Repeat.

454.name: Bird Dog on ball
