454.description: Raise arm and torso upward beside head while raising leg on opposite side up out behind body. Lower arm, torso, and leg to original position and repeat. Perform movement with opposite arm and leg.

455.name: Alternating
455.description: Raise left arm and torso upward beside head while raising right leg up behind body. Lower arm, torso, and leg to original position and repeat. Repeat by raising and lowering right arm and left leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between opposite sides.

456.name: Hanging Hyperextension
456.description: Raise hips up as high as possible by extending hips and spine. Lower hips to original position just above floor. Repeat.

457.name: Hyperextension
457.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

458.name: arms crossed
458.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

459.name: hands on head
459.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

460.name: Hyperextension (45°)
460.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

461.name: arms crossed
461.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

462.name: hands behind neck
462.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

463.name: arms up
463.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

464.name: Lunge
464.description: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

465.name: Rear Lunge
465.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

466.name: Reverse Hyper-extension
466.description: Raise legs by extending hips as high as possible until legs are nearly straight. Lower legs to original position. Repeat.

467.name: on ball
467.description: Holding firmly on anchor, extend legs upward by lifting and straightening leg as high as possible. Lower legs to original position with thighs close to stability ball. Repeat.

468.name: Single Leg Hip Bridge
468.description: Raise body by extending hip of bent leg, keeping extended leg and hip straight. Return to original position by lowering body with extended leg and hip straight. Repeat and continue with opposite sides.

469.name: Single Leg Squat
469.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back as straight as possible and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

470.name: Box
470.description: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once bottocks makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

471.name: Partial
471.description: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once buttock makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

472.name: Leg Back
472.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping raised leg from contacting floor as far down as possible. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. In lowest position, gently place elevated lower leg on floor. Raise body back up with minimal assistance from raised leg on floor. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

473.name: Half
473.description: Squat down to challenging depth while keeping raised leg from contacting floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Stand back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

474.name: Reclining
474.description: While reclining back, squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as suppor ting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

475.name: Split Squat
475.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

476.name: Single Leg Split Squat
476.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

477.name: Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift
477.description: Lower torso forward and downward while raising lifted leg back behind. Keep back straight and knee of supporting leg slightly bend. Keep hip and knee of lifted leg extended throughout movement. Once stretch is felt or hands contact floor, return to original position by raising torso while lowering lifted leg. Straighten knee of supporting leg as torso becomes upright. Repeat.

478.name: Squat
478.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

479.name: Half
479.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend to height which allows prescribed number of reps at suggested intensity, short of thighs descending just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

480.name: on Balance Board
480.description: Extend arms forward in front of body. Squat down by bending knees slightly forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

481.name: Step-up
481.description: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

482.name: Lateral Step-up
482.description: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg, alternating between legs.

483.name: Step Down
483.description: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

484.name: Alternating
484.description: Step down with first foot to side of elevated surface onto floor. Stand back up on elevated surface by straightening upper leg and pushing body upward. Place foot to original position next to opposite foot. Step down and back up with opposite leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between sides.

485.name: Side Bridge Hip Abduction
485.description: Keeping side of bottom foot on ground, raise hips up off ground while raising upper leg upward away from lower leg. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

486.name: Angled
486.description: Keeping foot closest to bar on ground, raise hips upward and away from bar while raising leg furthest from bar upward away from lower leg. Return to original position with hips sagging downward and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

487.name: Bent Knee
487.description: Keeping shank of lower leg on mat or floor, raise hips up off ground while raising upper leg upward away from lower leg. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

488.name: Angled Side Bridge
488.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

489.name: Bent Knee Side Bridge
489.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

491.name: Hanging Leg Raise
491.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

492.name: with ab straps
492.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

493.name: Straight Leg
493.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips are extended downward. Repeat.

494.name: Incline Leg Raise
494.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

495.name: arms on pads
495.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

496.name: Incline Straight Leg Raise
496.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

497.name: arms on pads
497.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

498.name: Lying Leg Raise
498.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

499.name: Alternating
499.description: Simultaneously change positions of legs, lowering and straightening raised leg down just above floor while raising and bending lower leg to opposite position. Continue alternating leg positions.

500.name: on floor
500.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

501.name: Lying Straight Leg Raise
501.description: Keeping knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

502.name: Alternating
502.description: Keeping knees nearly straight, simultaneously change positions of legs so vertical leg is lowered while lower leg is raised vertically. Continue alternating leg positions.

503.name: Seated Leg Raise
503.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees while pulling torso slightly forward to maintain balance. Return by extending hips and knees and lean torso back to counter balance. Repeat.

504.name: Vertical Leg Raise
504.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

505.name: on parallel bars
505.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

506.name: Straight Leg
506.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just pass parallel to floor. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

507.name: Jack-knife on Ball
507.description: Bend hips and knees, allowing shins to roll over top of ball. Pull knees toward chest until heels are under or near glutes. Return by extending hips and knees to original position. Repeat.

508.name: Roman Chair Sit-up
508.description: Lower body back until hips are almost extended. Raise body by flexing hips until torso is upright. Repeat.

509.name: Scissor Kick
509.description: Keeping knees nearly straight, simultaneously change positions of legs so vertical leg is lowered while lower leg is raised vertically. Continue alternating leg positions.

510.name: Jack-Knife
510.description: Bend hips and knees, pulling legs under body. Pull bent knees toward chest, allowing rear end to raise upward. Return by extending hips and knees to original position. Repeat.

511.name: Rollout
511.description: With arms straight, roll wheel out as far as possible. Lower body gently to floor extending arms forward. Raise body back up by flexing hips and pulling arms back to original position. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

512.name: Pike
512.description: From plank position, raise rear end up as high as possible by bending hips. Pull power wheel toward hands while keeping knees straight. Return by extending hips to original position.   Repeat.

513.name: Pike
513.description: From plank position, raise rear end up as high as possible by bending hips. Pull gliding discs toward hands while keeping knees straight. Return by extending hips to original position. Repeat.

514.name: Rear Lunge
514.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

515.name: Lunge
515.description: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

516.name: Single Leg Squat
516.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back as straight as possible and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

517.name: Box
517.description: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once buttock makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

518.name: Partial
518.description: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Once buttock makes contact with bench or box, raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

519.name: Leg Back
519.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping raised leg from contacting floor as far down as possible. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. In lowest position, gently place elevated lower leg on floor. Raise body back up with minimal assistance from raised leg on floor. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

520.name: Half
520.description: Squat down to challenging depth while keeping raised leg from contacting floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Stand back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

521.name: Reclining
521.description: While reclining back, squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep   back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

522.name: Sissy Squat
522.description: With hips and waist straight, bend knees to allow body to fall backwards as knees come forward. Allow heels to raise from floor. Lower body until knees are almost fully flexed or near floor. Return to original position by extending knees as heels return to floor.

523.name: on apparatus
523.description: Allow body to fall backwards by bending knees. During descent, gradually bend hips, yet keep chest high and don't allow torso to angle forward. Lower body until back of thigh is against upper pad. Rise to original position by extending knees and hips while keeping shoulders behind hips. Repeat.

524.name: Split Squat
524.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

525.name: Single Leg Split Squat
525.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

526.name: Squat
526.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

527.name: Half
527.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend to height which allows prescribed number of reps at suggested intensity, short of thighs descending just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

528.name: on Balance Board
528.description: Extend arms forward in front of body. Squat down by bending knees slightly forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

529.name: Step-up
529.description: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

530.name: Lateral Step-up
530.description: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side slightly forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg alternating between legs.

531.name: Step-down
531.description: Stand on elevated surface by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of elevated surface to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

532.name: Alternating
532.description: Step down with first foot to side of elevated surface onto floor. Stand back up on elevated surface by straightening upper leg and pushing body upward. Place foot to original position, next to opposite foot. Step down and back up with opposite leg in same manner. Repeat by alternating between sides.

533.name: Glute-Ham Raise
533.description: From upright position, lower body by straightening knees until body is horizontal. Continue to lower torso by bending hips until body is upside down. Raise torso by extending hips until fully extended. Continue to raise body by flexing knees until body is upright. Repeat.

534.name: hands behind hips
534.description: From upright position, lower body by straightening knees until body is horizontal. Continue to lower torso by bending hips until body is upside down. Raise torso by extending hips until fully extended. Continue to raise body by flexing knees until body is upright. Repeat.

535.name: Hanging Hamstring Bridge
535.description: Raise hips up as high as possible by extending hips. Lower hips to original position just above floor. Repeat.

536.name: Single Leg
536.description: Raise hips up as high as possible by extending hip and spine. Maintain bent position of lower leg allowing it to rise with hips. Lower hips along with bent lower leg to original position and repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

537.name: Hanging Hamstring Bridge Curl
537.description: Raise hips by extending hips. Before full hip extension, pull body toward feet by bending knees and hips. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees, then lowering hips to original position just above floor. Repeat.

538.name: Single Leg
538.description: Raise hip and bent lower leg up by extending hip of elevated leg. Maintain bent position of lower leg allowing it to rise with hips. Before full hip extension, pull body toward foot by bending knee and hip of elevated leg. Roll onto foot until knee is fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knee, then lowering hips and bent lower leg to original position just above floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg position.

539.name: Hanging Leg Curl
539.description: Pull body toward feet by bending knees and hips. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

540.name: Straight Hip
540.description: Pull body toward feet by bending knees while keeping hips straight. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees. Repeat.

541.name: Inverse Leg Curl
541.description: Lower body until horizontal by straightening knees. Raise body by flexing knees only allowing hips to bend slightly. Repeat.

542.name: Straight Leg (on ball)
542.description: Keeping hips and low back straight, bend knees, pulling heels toward rear end. Allow feet to rollup on to ball. Lower to original position by straightening knees. Repeat.

543.name: Single Leg
543.description: Keeping hips and low back straight, bend knee, pulling heel toward rear end while keeping other leg extended straight so it raises upward. Allow foot to rollup on to ball. Lower to original position by straightening knee until other leg makes contact with ball. Repeat.

544.name: power wheel
544.description: Keeping hips and low back straight, bend knees, pulling heels toward rear end. Raise up until lower legs are vertical. Lower to original position by straightening knees. Repeat.

545.name: Single Leg 45° Hyperextension
545.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until fully flexed. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

546.name: Angled Side Bridge
546.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

547.name: Bent Knee Side Bridge
547.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

549.name: Standing Calf Raise
549.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

550.name: Single Leg
550.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Lower heel by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

551.name: Single Leg Forward Angled Calf Raise
551.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Allow body to travel forward and upward in same direction as body is orientated. Lower heel allowing foot to come back down flat on floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

552.name: Reverse Calf Raise
552.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

553.name: Single Leg
553.description: Pull forefoot up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending foot until toes are pointed downward. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

554.name: 30 Degree Shrug
554.description:
Use a handle attachment on both sides of crossover. With cable attachment set all the way to the bottom.
Grab both handles and make sure you are centered in the machine. Let your arms hang freely.
Pull your shoulder blades up and in towards your ears. Let your shoulder blades depress back to the starting position.

555.name: Overhead Press
555.description:
Use a handle attachment with the cable set to the bottom of the machine. Stand upright making sure to maintain a flat back. Your starting position will have your palms facing forward.
Use both your elbows and shoulders to press the weight directly overhead.

556.name: Silverback Shrug
556.description:
Use a bar attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.
Stand up with the attachment in hand, walk a couple of steps back make sure you are standing upright and not leaning backwards.
Retract your shoulder blades and then protract to return to the starting position.

557.name: Upright Row
557.description:
Use a handle attachment with the cable set to the bottom of the machine.
Pull your elbows straight up toward the ceiling until the attachment is just below your chin then extend until your elbows are fully extended.

558.name: Behind Neck Press
558.description: Press cable bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return behind neck and repeat.

559.name: Front Raise
559.description: Raise cable bar forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

560.name: Military Press
560.description: Press cable bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

561.name: Shoulder Press
561.description: Press cable bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Return to upper chest and repeat.

562.name: Front Raise
562.description: Raise stirrups forward and upward until upper arms are well above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

563.name: Alternating
563.description: Raise one stirrup forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat with opposite arm, alternating between arms.

564.name: Seated
564.description: Raise one stirrup forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat with opposite arm. Continue by alternating raises between sides.

565.name: One Arm
565.description: Raise stirrup forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat. Repeat with opposite arm.

566.name: with rope
566.description: Raise stirrup forward and upward until arm is well above horizontal or cable makes contact with underside of upper arm. Lower and repeat. Repeat with opposite arm.

567.name: Shoulder Press
567.description: Push stirrups upward until arms are extended overhead. Return stirrups to sides of shoulders and repeat.

568.name: Seated
568.description: Push stirrups upward until arms are extended overhead. Return stirrups to sides of shoulders and repeat.

570.name: Lateral Raise
570.description: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms to sides   until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

571.name: One Arm
571.description: With elbow slightly bent, raise arm to side away from low pulley until elbow is shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

572.name: with close pulleys
572.description: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms to side until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

573.name: Seated
573.description: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms to side until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

574.name: Upright Row
574.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

575.name: Cable Bar
575.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

576.name: Dual Pulley
576.description: Pull handles up to front of shoulders with elbows leading and cables crossed. Allow wrists to flex as stirrups are lifted. Lower and repeat.

577.name: One Arm
577.description: Pull stirup to front side of shoulder with elbow leading. Allow wrist to flex as stirrup is lifted. Lower and repeat.

578.name: with rope
578.description: Pull rope ends to front of shoulders with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as stirrups are lifted. Lower and repeat.

580.name: Wide Grip
580.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

581.name: Y Raise
581.description: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms upward and outward to sides in Y configuration until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower stirrups forward and downward in reverse pattern. Repeat.

582.name: Seated
582.description: Raise arms upward and outward to sides in Y configuration while allowing elbows to partially bend. Pull back until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower stirrups forward and downward until arms are extended straight in front of body. Repeat.

583.name: with Rope
583.description: With torso upright pull rope upward over head until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower stirrups forward and downward until arms are extended straight in front of body. Repeat.

584.name: Reverse Fly
584.description: Pull stirrups out to sides, maintaining stiff elbow position throughout exercise. Return to original position and repeat.

585.name: Seated
585.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull stirrups out to sides, maintaining slightly bent elbow position throughout exercise. Return to original position and repeat.

586.name: One Arm
586.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull stirrup out to side, maintaining fixed elbow position throughout exercise. Return to original position and repeat. Repeat with other arm.

587.name: Supine
587.description: Pull upper arms down to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (just slightly bent) as arms are pulled down to sides. Return arms to original position and repeat.

588.name: Rear Delt Row
588.description: Pull cable attachment toward upper chest, just below neck, with elbows up out to sides until elbows travel slightly behind back. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

590.name: with rope
590.description: Pull rope to upper chest or neck, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Keep upper arms perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended forward. Repeat.

591.name: Stirrups
591.description: Pull stirrups out to sides, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Allow wrists to follow elbows. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

592.name: Seated
592.description: Pull stirrups out to sides, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Allow wrists to follow elbows. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

593.name: Standing
593.description: Pull stirrups out to sides, keeping elbows at shoulder height until elbows travel slightly behind back. Allow wrists to follow elbows. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

594.name: Rear Lateral Raise
594.description: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and slight bend in elbows as arms are raised to sides. Lower and repeat.

595.name: One Arm
595.description: Raise arm to side until elbow is shoulder height. Maintain upper arm perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat. Repeat with other arm.

596.name: Seated
596.description: Pull stirrups out to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower until arms contact sides of legs. Repeat.

597.name: Standing Cross Row
597.description: Pull both cable attachments by moving elbows back to sides. Keep upper arms horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return and repeat.

598.name: One Arm
598.description: Pull stirrup back with elbow up at shoulder height until elbow travels just behind shoulder. Keep upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to trunk. Return until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

599.name: Front Lateral Raise
599.description: With elbow straight or slightly bent, raise upper arm away from low pulley to side, slightly to front (30°) until upper arm is shoulder height. Lower and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

600.name: Seated
600.description: With elbows straight or slightly bent, raise upper arm away from low pulley to side, slightly to front (30° to 45°) until upper arm is shoulder height or slightly higher. Lower and repeat.

602.name: Decline Fly
602.description: Bring cable stirrups together above upper abdomen in hugging motion; elbows in fixed position and shoulders internally rotated so elbows are to sides. Return to starting position until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

603.name: Lying Fly
603.description: Bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position and shoulders internally rotated so elbows are to sides. Return to starting position until slight stretch. Repeat.

604.name: Seated Fly
604.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Return to starting position until slight stretch. Repeat.

605.name: Standing Fly
605.description: Bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

606.name: Bench Press
606.description: Push stirrups up over each shoulder until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

607.name: Cable Bar
607.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended. Lower bar to chest or until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

608.name: Chest Press
608.description: Push stirrups out straight until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

609.name: One Arm
609.description: Push stirrups out straight in front of shoulder until arm is straight. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt through shoulder or chest. Repeat.

610.name: Standing
610.description: Push stirrups forward until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

611.name: Cable Bar
611.description: Push cable bar forward until arms are straight. Return cable bar to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

612.name: Twisting
612.description: Push stirrup out in front of upper chest while turning torso away from pulley. Return stirrup and torso back to original position allowing torso to rotate back until slight stretch is felt through chest, shoulder or waist. Repeat.

613.name: Decline Chest Press
613.description: Push stirrups forward and slightly downward until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in shoulders or chest. Repeat.

614.name: Bar
614.description: Push cable bar forward and downward until bar is about hip height and arms are straight. Return cable bar to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

615.name: Standing
615.description: Push stirrups at forward/downward angle until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

616.name: Twisting Standing Chest Press
616.description: Push stirrups away from body, horizontally until arm is straight and inline with cable. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

617.name: Incline Bench Press
617.description: Push stirrups up over each shoulder until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

618.name: Cable Bar
618.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended. Lower bar to upper chest or until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

619.name: Incline Chest Press
619.description: Push stirrups away from body, slightly upward at 30º to 45º until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

620.name: Standing Incline Chest Press
620.description: Push stirrups forward and upward at 30º to 45º angle until arms are straight and parallel to one another. Return stirrups to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

621.name: Cable Bar
621.description: Push cable bar forward and upward at 30º to 45º until arms are straight. Return cable bar to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Repeat.

622.name: One Arm
622.description: Push stirrups forward and upward at 30º to 45º until arm is straight and in-line with cable. Return stirrup to original position until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

623.name: Incline Fly
623.description: Lower stirrups outward to sides of shoulders. Keep elbows fixed in slightly bent position. When a stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, bring stirrups back together in hugging motion above upper chest until stirrups are nearly together Repeat.

624.name: Standing Incline Fly
624.description: Keeping elbows fixed in slightly bent position, bring stirrups together in upwardly arching, hugging motion, at 30º to 45º angle until they meet at top of motion. Lower stirrups to original position in reverse pattern. As soon as stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, repeat motion.

625.name: Standing Fly
625.description: Bring cable attachments together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

626.name: Incline Shoulder Raise
626.description: Raise shoulders toward stirrups as high as possible. Lower shoulders down and back and repeat.

627.name: One Arm Incline Push
627.description: Push stirrup forward and up at 30º to 45º while rotating torso away allowing shoulder to be extended forward. Return stirrups to original position, until slight stretch, and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

628.name: Bayesian Curl
628.description:
Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Face away from the cable machine.
Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support. Face your palm forward. Flex at the elbow and extend.

629.name: Hammer Curl
629.description:
Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Use a neutral grip thumb facing up pinky-facing down). Flex at the elbow and extend.

630.name: Twisting Curl
630.description:
Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Start with a neutral grip. Flex at the elbow. While flexing twist your palm. When you hit the top of the movement your palm should be facing upward.

631.name: Reverse Curl
631.description:
Use a handle attachment. The cable should be set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Face away from the cable machine. Stagger your stance so you have a better base of support.
Face your palm downwards. Flex at the elbow and extend.

632.name: Hammer Curl
632.description: With elbows to side, raise rope forward and upward with both arms until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

633.name: Reverse Curl
633.description: With elbows to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

634.name: Cable Bar
634.description: With elbows to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

635.name: Reverse Preacher Curl
635.description: Raise cable bar toward shoulders. Lower cable bar until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

636.name: Standing
636.description: Raise cable bar toward shoulders. Lower cable bar until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

637.name: Wrist Curl
637.description: Allow cable bar to roll out of palms down to fingers. Raise cable bar back up by gripping and pointing knuckles up as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

638.name: One Arm
638.description: Allow cable bar to roll out of palms down to fingers. Raise cable bar back up by gripping and pointing knuckles up as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

639.name: Wrist Roller
639.description: With left hand gripping handle, relax grip of right hand and slide grip behind handle (by hypexending wrist) and regrip. Relax grip of left hand and flex right wrist. Repeat sequence with opposite hands, alternating back and forth until weight plate has raised up near hands. Lower weight steadily with opposite movement.

640.name: Reverse Wrist Curl
640.description: Raise stirrup by pointing knuckles upward as high as possible. Return until knuckles are pointing downward as far as possible. Repeat.

641.name: One Arm
641.description: Raise stirrup by pointing knuckles upward as high as possible. Return until knuckles are pointing downward as far as possible. Repeat.

642.name: Wrist Roller
642.description: With left hand gripping handle, relax grip of right hand and slide grip in front of handle (by flexing wrist) and regrip. Relax grip of left hand and hyperextend right wrist. Repeat sequence with opposite hands, alternating back and forth until weight plate has raised up near hands. Lower weight steadily with opposite movement.

643.name: Goblet Squat
643.description:
Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .
Get your elbows directly underneath the bar, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.
Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.
Squat all the way back to a standing position.

644.name: Split Squat
644.description:
You can use any attachment on this exercise. Cable should be set all to the bottom.
Grab the attachment and walk back a few steps. Take a split stance. One leg in front and one behind.
Break at the knees and hips to initiate the split squat. Make sure your back knee touches the floor.
Squat back up into a standing position.

645.name: Standing Calf Raise
645.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

646.name: Single Leg
646.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Lower heel by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat.

647.name: One Arm
647.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Lower heel by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat.

648.name: Reverse Calf Raise
648.description: Pull forefeet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

649.name: Single Leg
649.description: Pull forefoot up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

650.name: 30 Degree Shrug
650.description:
Use a handle attachment on both sides of crossover. With cable attachment set all the way to the bottom.
Grab both handles and make sure you are centered in the machine. Let your arms hang freely.
Pull your shoulder blades up and in towards your ears. Let your shoulder blades depress back to the starting position.

651.name: Silverback Shrug
651.description:
Use a bar attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.
Stand up with the attachment in hand, walk a couple of steps back make sure you are standing upright and not leaning backwards.
Retract your shoulder blades and then protract to return to the starting position.

652.name: Pushdown
652.description:
You can use any attachment for this. The cable should be set all the way at the top of the machine.
Make sure to keep your upper arm glued at your side. Extend your elbows until you feel your triceps contract.

653.name: Skullcrusher
653.description:
You can use a straight bar, rope, easy bar, or two handles. The cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.
Face away from the machine with your elbows up and the attachment just behind your head.
Extend at the elbows until you feel a contraction in your triceps and then flex at the elbow back to the starting position.

654.name: Cross Pushdown
654.description:
Either use two handles or no attachment at all. Both sides of the cable crossover should be set to the top.
Stand in the center of the machine holding each Cable in the opposing hand. Your upper arm should be at a 45 degree angle with your torso.
Extend your elbows until you feel a contraction and then return to the starting position

655.name: Overhead Tricep Extension
655.description:
You can use any attachment. The cable should be all the way to the bottom of the machine. Face away from the machine.
Point your elbows straight up toward the ceiling.
From there, extend your elbows until your fists are pointed straight toward the ceiling.

656.name: Pullover
656.description:
You can use any attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.
Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward somewhat.
Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. Imagine trying to pull the attachment through your thighs at the bottom.

657.name: Pull - In
657.description:
Use a handle attachment set all the way to the top of the cable crossover machine.
Walk a few steps away from the cable machine. Face your body sideways.
Face your palm up toward the ceiling. Then pull your elbow in toward your rib cage.

658.name: Lat Prayer
658.description:
You can use any attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the top of the machine.
Grab your attachment and walk a few steps back. Push your butt back to where you are leaning forward. Your ears should be between your arms.
Initiate the movement with your shoulders and not your elbows. As you flex at the shoulder joint push your hips forward until your hips meet the attachment.

659.name: Goblet Squat
659.description:
Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .
Get your elbows directly underneath the bar, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.
Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.
Squat all the way back to a standing position.

660.name: Romanian Deadlift
660.description:
Start with a straight bar or ez bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back
Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

661.name: Glute Kickback
661.description:
Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to the bottom of the crossover machine.
Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

662.name: Single Leg Deadlift
662.description:
Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.
Push your butt back to initiate the movement while lifting one of your legs.
Then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Compete your given amount of reps, then switch to opposite leg.
To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back.

663.name: Romanian Deadlift
663.description:
Start with a straight bar or ez bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back
Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

664.name: Goblet Squat
664.description:
Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment .
Get your elbows directly underneath the bar, squat straight up and then walk back a few steps.
Break at your knees and hips to initiate the squat. Make sure you maintain a flat back.
Squat all the way back to a standing position.

665.name: Glute Kickback
665.description:
Use an ankle attachment. The cable should be set to the bottom of the crossover machine.
Push your ankle straight back, extending at the hip. Hold for a one count when you feel a contraction in your glutes.
Then flex at the hips until you are back into your original position.

666.name: Hip Abduction
666.description:
Use an ankle attachment. Cable should be set all the way to the bottom.
Face sideways with the ankle attachment on your outside leg. Walk a few steps away.
Abduct at the hips and raise your leg out to the side.
Return to the starting position and stop just short of your foot touching back to the ground (to keep tension on the muscle).

667.name: Romanian Deadlift
667.description:
Start with a straight bar or ez bar attachment set to the bottom of the machine. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back
Push your butt back to initiate the movement and then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back on any exercise.

668.name: Hamstring Curl
668.description:
Use an ankle attachment with the cable set all the way to the bottom of the machine.
Stand upright or try bending slightly forward.
Flex at the knee and pull your ankle straight back.

669.name: Single Leg Deadlift
669.description:
Start with a straight bar or easy bar attachment. Squat the weight up into a standing position and walk a few steps back.
Push your butt back to initiate the movement while lifting one of your legs.
Then push your butt forward until you're back in a standing position.
Compete your given amount of reps, then switch to opposite leg.
To protect yourself from injury, always maintain a flat back.

670.name: Pull Through
670.description:
This exercise works best with a rope attachment but can be done with anything. The attachment should be set to the bottom of the machine.
Face away from the cable machine, straddle the cable itself, and grab the attachment.
Walk a few steps away.
Break at the hips while maintaining a flat back and mostly extended knees.
Push hips forward until you are back in a standing position.

671.name: Glute Kickback
671.description: Pull cable attachment back by extending hip and knee. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

672.name: Rear Lunge
672.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

673.name: Step-down
673.description: Extend one leg back on forefoot. Lower body on other leg by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with lower platform. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating rear lunge with opposite leg.

674.name: Single Leg Split Squat
674.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

675.name: One Arm
675.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

676.name: Split Squat
676.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

677.name: Two Arms
677.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

678.name: One Arm
678.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

679.name: Squat
679.description: Keeping chest high and back straight, raise stirrups by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Squat down until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

680.name: Cable Bar Squat
680.description: Stand up by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Squat back down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend slightly forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

681.name: Belt Squat
681.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

682.name: Standing Hip Extension
682.description: Pull cable attachment back by extending hip. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

683.name: Bent-over
683.description: Pull cable attachment back by extending hip. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

684.name: Step-up
684.description: Place foot of first leg on elevated platform. Stand on elevated platform by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to lower position. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

685.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
685.description: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

686.name: Straight-back
686.description: With back straight, bow forward by bending hips and bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso by extending hips while gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

687.name: Hip Abduction
687.description: Move leg to opposite side of low pulley by abduction hip. Return and repeat. Turn around and continue with opposite leg.

688.name: Lying Hip Internal Rotation
688.description: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment away from pulley by rotating hip as far as possible. Return leg to original position toward pulley and repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue lying opposite direction.

689.name: Seated Hip Internal Rotation
689.description: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment away from pulley by rotating hip as far as possible. Return foot behind stationary foot and toward pulley. Repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue facing opposite direction.

691.name: Lying Leg Raise
691.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are just past perpendicular to torso or before hips raise off of bench. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

692.name: on bench
692.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are past perpendicular to torso or before hips raise off of bench. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

693.name: Straight Leg
693.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past perpendicular to torso or before hips raise off of mat. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

694.name: Standing Leg Raise
694.description: Raise knee by flexing hip while allowing lower leg to bend back under resistance. When thigh is just beyond horizontal, lower leg until hip and knee is extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

695.name: Straight Leg
695.description: Raise leg upward by flexing hip while keeping knee straight. Raise leg as high as possible. Lower leg to original starting position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

696.name: Lying Hip External Rotation
696.description: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment toward opposite knee by rotating hip. Return until slight stretch is felt in hip, then repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue lying opposite direction.

697.name: Seated Hip External Rotation
697.description: Keeping knee of attached leg bent approximately 90°, pull cable attachment under thigh of stationary leg by rotating hip. Return until slight stretch is felt in hip, then repeat. Place ankle cuff on opposite leg and continue facing opposite direction.

698.name: Neck Flexion
698.description: Move head away from pulley by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Return head by hyperextending neck and repeat.

699.name: with belt
699.description: Pull head forward and down by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return by hyperextending neck until head is angled upward. Repeat.

700.name: Neck Rotation (with belt)
700.description: Turn head away from pulley cable by rotating head away from pulley. Turn head back toward cable pulley and repeat. Turn seat the opposite direction or attach belt to pulley on opposite side and continue with other side.

701.name: Lateral Neck Flexion (with belt)
701.description: Pull head away from pulley cable by laterally flexing neck. Tilt head back toward cable pulley and repeat. Sit on bench the opposite direction and continue with other side.

702.name: Neck Extension
702.description: Move head away from pulley by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

703.name: with belt
703.description: Pull head up and back by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

704.name: Bent-over Triceps Extension
704.description: Extend forearms forward until elbows are straight. Allow cable bar to return back over neck. Repeat.

705.name: Cable Bar
705.description: Extend forearms forward until elbows are straight. Allow cable bar to return back over neck. Repeat.

706.name: with rope attachment
706.description: Extend forearms forward until elbows are straight. Allow cable bar to return back over neck. Repeat.

707.name: Forward Triceps Extension
707.description: Push stirrup forward by extending forearm until elbow is straight. Allow stirrup to return back over shoulder. Repeat and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

708.name: Incline Triceps Extension
708.description: Extend forearm overhead until elbows are straight. Lower until forearms are against upper arms. Repeat.

709.name: Kneeling Triceps Extension
709.description: Extend forearms over head until elbow are fully extended. Return and repeat.

710.name: Lying Triceps Extension
710.description: Lower bar by bending elbow. As bar nears head, move elbows slightly back just enough to allow bar to clear around curvature of head. Extend arm. As bar clears head, reposition elbows to its former position until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

711.name: Cable Bar
711.description: Lower cable bar by bending elbow. As cable bar nears head, move elbows slightly back just enough to allow cable bar to clear around curvature of head. Extend arm. As cable bar clears head, reposition elbows to its former position until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

712.name: Decline
712.description: Extend elbows to raise bar attachment until arms are straight. As arms extended, position them vertically. Lower bar by bending elbows. As bar nears head, reposition elbows back just enough to allow bar to clear around curvature of head. Repeat.

713.name: Pushdown
713.description: Extend arms down. Return until forearm is close to upper arm. Repeat.

714.name: Alternating Seated
714.description: Push one stirrup down by extending elbow until arm is straight. Return until forearm returns to original positon, keeping elbow close to side. Repeat with opposite arm and alternate.

715.name: Cable Bar
715.description: Extend arms down. Return until forearm is close to upper arm. Repeat.

716.name: forward leaning
716.description: Push cable bar downward by extending arms until elbows are straight. Return to front of face until forearms are nearly vertical and close to upper arm. Repeat.

717.name: Cable Bar
717.description: Push cable bar downward by extending arms until elbows are straight. Return to front of face until forearms are nearly vertical and close to upper arm. Repeat.

718.name: Incline
718.description: Extend arms with elbows stationary. Return until forearm is close to upper arm. Repeat.

719.name: One Arm
719.description: Extend arm down. Return until forearm is close to upper arm. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

720.name: with back support
720.description: Extend arms down. Return until forearm is close to upper arm. Repeat.

721.name: with rope attachment
721.description: Extend arms down. Turn palms down at bottom. Return until forearm is close to upper arm and hands are in original position. Repeat.

722.name: with V-bar attachment
722.description: Extend arms down. Return until forearm is close to upper arm. Repeat.

723.name: Side Triceps Extension
723.description: Push stirrup out to side by extending forearm until elbow is straight. Allow stirrup to return back over shoulder. Repeat and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

724.name: Triceps Dip
724.description: Lower body by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

725.name: Triceps Extension
725.description: Raise cable bar overhead by extending elbows until arms are positioned straight and vertical. Lower cable bar behind neck by flexing elbows allowing forearms to travel behind upper arms with elbows remaining overhead. Repeat.

726.name: One Arm (pronated)
726.description: Extend arm upward. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

727.name: One Arm (supinated)
727.description: Extend arm upward. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

728.name: with rope
728.description: Raise ends of rope overhead by extending forearms until arms are straight. Lower rope attachment until forearms are against upper arms. Repeat.

729.name: Alternating Curl
729.description: Pull one stirrup up forward and upward toward shoulder while keeping elbow stationary. Return until arm is fully extended. Repeat on other arm, alternating between sides.

730.name: Seated
730.description: Pull one stirrup up toward shoulder while keeping elbow stationary. Return until arm is fully extended. Repeat with other arm, alternating between sides.

731.name: Curl
731.description: With elbows to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

732.name: Cable Bar
732.description: With elbows to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

733.name: with stirrups
733.description: Pull stirrups forward and upward toward shoulders while keeping elbows stationary. Return until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

734.name: Seated
734.description: Pull both stirrups up toward shoulders while keeping elbows stationary. Return until arms are fully extended and repeat.

735.name: One Arm Curl
735.description: With elbow to side, raise bar until forearms are vertical. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

736.name: Supine Curl
736.description: With elbows to side, pull bar until elbows are flexed. Lower until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

737.name: Concentration Curl
737.description: Pull stirrup to front of shoulder until elbow is completely flexed. Lower stirrup until arm is fully extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

738.name: Preacher Curl
738.description: Raise cable bar toward shoulders. Lower cable bar until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

739.name: Alternating
739.description: Raise one stirrup upward toward shoulder of same arm. Lower stirrup until arm is fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue alternating between arms.

740.name: Standing
740.description: Raise cable bar toward shoulders. Lower cable bar until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

741.name: One Arm
741.description: Raise stirrup upward toward shoulder of same arm. Lower stirrup until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

742.name: One Arm
742.description: Raise stirrup upward toward shoulder of same arm. Lower stirrup until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

743.name: Stirrups
743.description: Raise both stirrups upward toward shoulders. Lower stirrups until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

745.name: Incline Row
745.description: Pull cable attachment to waist while straightening back upright. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

746.name: Straight Back
746.description: Pull cable attachment to waist. Pull shoulders back and lift chest by arching back. Return until arms are extended, back is straight and perpendicular to incline, and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

747.name: Kneeling Row
747.description: Pull stirrup up to side until elbow travels beyond surface of back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched downward. Repeat and continue with opposite side.

748.name: Lying Row
748.description: Pull stirrups down to each side of chest until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched upward. Repeat.

749.name: One Arm Bent-over Row
749.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso, pulling shoulder back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

750.name: One Arm Seated Row
750.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso, slightly twisting through waist. Pull shoulder back and push chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

751.name: Twisting
751.description: Pull cable attachment to side, extending and twisting through waist. Pull shoulders back and sit upright while pushing chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat and perform exercise with opposite arm.

752.name: One Arm Seated High Row
752.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso, straightening back and leaning back slightly. Pull shoulder back and push chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and torso is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

753.name: Straight Back
753.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso while pulling shoulder back, arching spine, and pushing chest forward. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

755.name: Seated High Row
755.description: Pull cable attachment to waist and lean back slightly. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until torso, arms, and shoulders pulled forward. Repeat.

756.name: Alternating
756.description: Pull one cable stirrup to side. Pull shoulder back, push chest forward, and rotate body slightly toward pulling arm. Return until arm is extended and torso faces forward. Pull with opposite arm alternating between each side. Repeat.

757.name: Seated Row
757.description: Pull cable attachment to waist while straightening lower back. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

758.name: Straight Back
758.description: Pull cable attachment to waist. Pull shoulders back and lift chest by arching back. Return until arms are extended, back is straight, and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

759.name: Seated Wide Grip Row
759.description: Pull cable attachment to waist while pulling torso upright.   Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

760.name: Straight Back
760.description: Pull cable attachment to waist. Pull shoulders back and lift chest by arching back. Return until arms are extended, back is straight, and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

761.name: One Arm Standing Row
761.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso while pulling shoulder back, arching spine, and pushing chest forward. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

762.name: Low Row
762.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso while pulling shoulder back, arching spine, and pushing chest forward. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

763.name: Twisting Standing High Row
763.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso and rotate body toward side of pulling arm. Pull shoulder back and push chest forward. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

764.name: Close Grip Pulldown
764.description: Pull down cable attachment to upper chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

765.name: Alternating
765.description: Pull down one cable attachment to side of chest. Return until arm and shoulder is fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

766.name: One Arm
766.description: Pull down cable attachment to side of chest. Return until arm and shoulder is fully extended, allowing shoulder to raise. Repeat and continue with other arm.

767.name: Kneeling
767.description: Pull down cable attachment to side of chest. Return until arm and shoulder is fully extended, allowing shoulder to raise. Repeat and continue with other arm.

768.name: with Stirrups
768.description: Pull down cable attachments to sides of chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

769.name: Kneeling Bent-over Pulldown
769.description: Pull cable rope down until elbows are back and inside of rope attachment is behind neck. Return attachment over head until shoulder is completely flexed upward. Repeat.

770.name: Pulldown
770.description: Pull down cable bar to upper chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

771.name: Alternating
771.description: Pull down one cable attachment to front side shoulder. Return until arm and shoulder are fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

772.name: Parallel Grip Pulldown
772.description: Pull down cable attachment to upper chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

773.name: Pro Lat Bar
773.description: Pull down cable bar to upper chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

774.name: with Stirrups
774.description: Pull down cable attachments to front sides of shoulders. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

775.name: Pullover
775.description: Lower cable attachment toward pulley with elbows bent only slightly. Lower until shoulders are fully flexed or upper arms are in-line with upper torso. Raise cable attachment over head and continue toward lower body until cable becomes very close to head. Repeat.

776.name: Bent-over
776.description: With elbows fixed approximately 30°, pull cable attachment down until upper arms are to sides. Return attachment overhead. Repeat.

777.name: Seated
777.description: With elbows fixed with slight bend, pull cable attachment forward and down as far as possible. Return cable attachment forward and overhead. Repeat.

778.name: Chinup
778.description: Pull body up until elbow are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

779.name: Parallel Close Grip Pull-up
779.description: Pull body up until elbow are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

781.name: Pull-up
781.description: Pull body up until chin is above bar. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

782.name: Rear Pull-up
782.description: Pull body up until bar touches back of neck. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

783.name: Rear Pulldown
783.description: Pull cable bar down behind neck. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

784.name: Alternating
784.description: Pull down one cable attachment to front of shoulder. Return until arm and shoulder are fully extended. Repeat movement with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

785.name: Simultaneous
785.description: Pull down left cable attachment to front of shoulder. Pull right cable attachment down to front of other shoulder while returning left cable attachment to front of shoulder. Repeat movement with both arms in opposite pattern by pulling left cable attachment while returning right pully attachment. Continuing by alternating movement pattern between sides.

786.name: Twisting Overhead Pull
786.description: Pull down cable attachment to side of chest and rotate body toward side of pulling arm. Return until arm and shoulder is fully extended, allowing shoulder to raise. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

787.name: Underhand Pulldown
787.description: Pull down cable bar to upper chest until elbows are to sides. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

788.name: Shrug
788.description: With arms straight, elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

789.name: Cable Bar
789.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

790.name: Dual Pulley
790.description: With arms straight, elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

791.name: Shrug with Stirrups
791.description: With arms straight, elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

792.name: One Arm
792.description: With arms straight, elevate shoulder as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

793.name: Seated Shoulder External Rotation
793.description: Pull cable attachment away from body by externally rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Turn around and continue with opposite arm.

794.name: Standing
794.description: Pull cable attachment away from body as far as possible by externally rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Turn around and continue with opposite arm.

795.name: Upright Shoulder External Rotation
795.description: Pull stirrup up and back as far as possible. Return by lowering stirrup to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

796.name: Seated Shoulder Internal Rotation
796.description: Pull cable stirrup toward body by internally rotating shoulder until forearm is across belly. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

797.name: Standing Shoulder Internal Rotation
797.description: Pull cable stirrup toward body by internally rotating shoulder until forearm is across belly. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

798.name: Lying Crunch on ball
798.description: With hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel toward thighs. Return and repeat.

799.name: Lying Leg-Hip Raise
799.description: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Raise hips from floor by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

800.name: on bench
800.description: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Raise hips from floor by flexing waist. Return until legs are extended horizontally. Repeat.

801.name: Straight Leg
801.description: Raise legs by flexing hips until fully flexed. Raise hips from floor by flexing waist. Return until waist and hips are extended downward. Repeat.

802.name: Kneeling Crunch
802.description: With hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel toward middle of thighs. Return and repeat.

803.name: Seated Crunch
803.description: With hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel toward hips. Return and repeat.

804.name: Overhead
