804.description: With arms fixed in place, flex waist so shoulders travel forward and downward toward thighs. Return until chest is high and back is hyperextended. Repeat.

805.name: plate loaded
805.description: With hips stationary, flex waist small of back pushes into back of seat as upper back travels forward. Return and repeat.

806.name: Standing Crunch
806.description: Flex waist so torso pulls ropes forward and downward. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat alternating twists with opposite sides.

807.name: Overhead (rope)
807.description: With knees and hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel toward middle of thighs. Return and repeat.

808.name: Overhead (multi Bar)
808.description: With knees and hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel toward middle of thighs. Return and repeat.

809.name: Standing Twisting Crunch
809.description: Flex and twist spine so torso pulls strap forward and downward while twisting one shoulder to forward center. Return until back of shoulders return to back pad. Repeat alternating twists with opposite sides.

810.name: Kneeling Twisting Crunch
810.description: With hips stationary, flex waist to one side so elbow travels toward mid-thigh on opposite side. Return to original position and repeat on opposite side. Continue by alternating between sides.

811.name: Russian Twist (on ball)
811.description: Allow resistance from cable to turn torso downward, toward direction of pulley while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Pull stirrup in an arch over shoulders by rotating torso to opposite direction of pulley until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position in opposite direction and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

812.name: Side Bend
812.description: Pull stirrup by bending sideways through waist so torso moves away from pulley. Lower stirrup by leaning torso toward pulley. Repeat. Continue with opposite side.

813.name: Side Crunch
813.description: Pull stirrup downward by bending toward cable column through waist so torso moves toward base of cable column. Bend in opposite direction by leaning torso away from cable column, allowing stirrup to rise upward. Repeat. Continue with opposite side.

814.name: Seated Twist
814.description: Keeping arms straight, rotate torso to opposite side until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

815.name: Cross Arm
815.description: Rotate torso through waist to face opposite side until slight stretch if felt. Return to original side until slight stretch is felt. Repeat. Continue with opposite side.

816.name: Standing Twisting Crunch
816.description: Flex and twist spine so torso pulls strap forward and downward while twisting one shoulder to forward center. Return until back of shoulders return to back pad. Repeat alternating twists with opposite sides.

817.name: Single Side
817.description: Flex and twist spine so shoulder pulls strap diagonally forward and downward away from pulley. Return until back of shoulder returns to back pad and repeat.

818.name: Twist
818.description: Keeping arms straight, rotate torso to opposite side until cable makes contact with shoulder. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

819.name: Down Up
819.description: Keeping arms straight, pull stirrup diagonally upward around shoulders by rotating torso and raising arms gradually upward until cable makes contact with side of body. Bend knees slightly more as stirrup approaches top. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

820.name: Up Down
820.description: Keeping arms straight, pull stirrup diagonally downward around shoulders by rotating torso and gradually lowering arms downward until cable is just above shoulder. Gradually bend knees as stirrup makes its way around body and approaches bottom. Return to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

821.name: Push Pull
821.description: Pull low pulley stirrup back to side of ribcage while pushing high pulley stirrup forward until arm is extended, allowing torso to rotate to opposite side.

822.name: One Arm Row
822.description: Pull cable attachment to side, extending and twisting through waist. Pull shoulders back and sit upright while pushing chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat and perform exercise with opposite arm.

823.name: One Arm High Row
823.description: Pull cable attachment to side of torso, straightening back and leaning back slightly. Pull shoulder back and push chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and torso is pulled forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

824.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
824.description: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

825.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
825.description: With knees straight, bow forward by bending hips. Bend waist as stirrups approach lowest position. Lift dumbbells by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

826.name: Seated Row
826.description: Pull cable attachment to waist while straightening lower back. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

827.name: Wide Grip
827.description: Pull cable attachment to waist while pulling torso upright.   Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

828.name: Rear Lunge
828.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

829.name: Step-down
829.description: Extend one leg back on forefoot. Lower body on other leg by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with lower platform. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating rear lunge with opposite leg.

830.name: Single Leg Split Squat
830.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

831.name: One Arm
831.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

832.name: Split Squat
832.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly, until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

833.name: Two Arms
833.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

834.name: One Arm
834.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original straddle position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with legs in opposite position.

835.name: Squat
835.description: Keeping chest high and back straight, raise stirrups by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Squat down until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

836.name: Cable Bar Squat
836.description: Stand up by extending hips and knees until legs are straight. Squat back down to original squat position by bending hips back and knees forward while keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

837.name: Belt Squat
837.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

838.name: Half
838.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until weight stack taps or comes very close from making contact. Keeping chest high and back straight, raise back up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

839.name: Standing Leg Extension
839.description: Keeping thigh stationary, extend lower leg forward until leg is straight. Return by lowering lower leg down and back to original position. Repeat.

840.name: Step Down
840.description: Raise body by extending knee and hip on platform until leg is straight. Return until foot of lower leg makes contact with lower platform or floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

841.name: Step-up
841.description: Place foot of first leg on elevated platform. Stand on elevated platform by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to lower position. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

842.name: Bent-over Leg Curl
842.description: Pull cable attachment back and up slightly by flexing knee. Raise knee slightly by flexing hip until knee is fully flexed. Return by straightening knee and lowering knee slightly to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

843.name: Lying Leg Curl
843.description: Raise ankles to glutes by flexing knees. Lower ankles until knees are straight. Repeat.

844.name: Standing Leg Curl
844.description: Pull cable attachment back by flexing knee until knee is fully flexed. Return by straightening knee to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

845.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
845.description: With knees straight, bow forward by bending hips. Bend waist as stirrups approach lowest position. Lift stirrups by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

846.name: Straight-back
846.description: With knees and back straight, bow forward by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Raise body upright by extending hips until standing. Pull shoulders back slightly at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

847.name: Hip Adduction
847.description: Move near leg just in front of far leg by abduction hip. Return and repeat. Turn around and continue with opposite leg.

848.name: Lying Hip Adduction
848.description: Lower legs apart out to each side until stretch is felt in inner thigh. Raise legs together. Return and repeat.

849.name: Neck Flexion
849.description: Move head forward by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return head by hyperextending neck and repeat.

850.name: Lateral Neck Flexion
850.description: Move head down to side by laterally flexing neck. Return head to opposite side and repeat. Sit in machine backwards and continue with opposite side.

851.name: Neck Extension
851.description: Move head back by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck forward until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

852.name: Behind Neck Press
852.description: Press levers upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

853.name: Barbell Machine
853.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar behind neck and repeat.

854.name: Military Press
854.description: Press lever until arms are extended upward. Lower and repeat.

855.name: Reclined Shoulder Press
855.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Lower and repeat.

856.name: Shoulder Press
856.description: Press lever upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

857.name: Barbell Machine
857.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar to front of shoulders and repeat.

858.name: One Arm
858.description: Press end of barbell upward and forward until arm is extended. Lower to shoulder and repeat. Repeat with opposite side.

859.name: Barbell Machine Upright Row
859.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

860.name: Lateral Raise
860.description: Raise arms to sides until upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

861.name: Incline Rear Delt Row
861.description: Pull lever with elbows forward  out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

862.name: Lying Rear Lateral Raise
862.description: Pull arms up until elbows are beyond back. Return and repeat.

863.name: Rear Delt Raise
863.description: Pull lever up as far as possible allowing elbows to travel up behind body to each side. Lower until arms are straight and repeat.

864.name: Seated Rear Delt Row
864.description: Pull lever with elbows up out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

865.name: alternative machine
865.description: Pull lever with elbows up out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

866.name: Seated Rear Lateral Raise
866.description: Pull lever handles out to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat.

867.name: T-Bar Rear Delt Row
867.description: With elbows out to sides, pull bar up toward upper chest until elbows are same height as shoulders or just beyond, keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

869.name: Barbell Machine
869.description: Lower weight to chest with elbows close to body. Push barbell back up until arms are straight. Repeat.

870.name: Triceps Extension
870.description: Push lever down until arms are fully extended. Return and repeat.

871.name: no seat
871.description: Push lever down until arms are fully extended. Return and repeat.

872.name: Triceps Dip
872.description: Push levers down with elbows pointing back. Allow lever bar to raise until shoulders are slightly stretched. Repeat.

873.name: Preacher Curl
873.description: Raise lever handles toward shoulders. Lower handles until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

874.name: arms high
874.description: Pull lever handles toward shoulders. Return handles until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

875.name: Alternating
875.description: Pull one lever handle toward shoulder. Return handle until arm is fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue alternating movement between arms.

876.name: Standing
876.description: Raise lever handles toward shoulders. Lower handles until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

877.name: Grip
877.description: Squeeze bars together with both hands until lower lever makes contact with upper bars. Lower to original position and repeat.

878.name: Wrist Curl
878.description: Raise bar up until wrist is fully flexed. Lower and repeat.

879.name: Reverse Wrist Curl
879.description: Raise bar until wrist is fully hyperextended and return until wrist is fully flexed. Repeat.

881.name: Barbell Machine
881.description: Pull bar to waist. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

882.name: One Arm
882.description: Pull lever bar up to side until bar contacts shoulder or just until elbow travels behind height of back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched downward. Repeat and continue with opposite arm.

883.name: Wide Grip
883.description: Pull lever handles up to sides. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

884.name: Incline Row
884.description: Pull lever up as high as possible. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

885.name: Close Grip
885.description: Pull lever up as high as possible. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

886.name: One Arm Standing Row
886.description: Pull lever to side while twisting torso toward opposite side. Pull shoulder back and push chest forward during contraction. Return until arm is extended and torso is pulled toward original direction. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

887.name: Narrow Grip
887.description: Pull levers back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

888.name: Alternating
888.description: Pull one lever back until elbow is behind back and shoulder is pulled back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

889.name: Wide Grip
889.description: Pull levers back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

890.name: Alternating
890.description: Pull one lever back until elbow is behind back and shoulder is pulled back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

891.name: Low Bar
891.description: Pull levers back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

892.name: Seated Row (no chest pad)
892.description: Pull handles to waist while straightening torso upright. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

894.name: Seated Low Row
894.description: Pull levers back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

895.name: Seated High Row
895.description: Pull lever back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

896.name: Underhand Seated Row
896.description: Pull levers back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

897.name: Alternating
897.description: Pull one lever back until elbow is behind back and shoulder is pulled back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

902.name: Close Grip Pulldown
902.description: Pull down handles to sides of chest while leaning back slightly. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

903.name: Front Pulldown
903.description: Pull down lever bar to upper chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

904.name: Pulldown
904.description: Pull levers down to sides of shoulders. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

905.name: Pullover
905.description: Pull lever forward and down until elbows are to sides. Return until shoulders are fully flexed, or upper arms are parallel to torso. Repeat.

906.name: Rear Pulldown
906.description: Pull lever bar down behind neck. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

907.name: Underhand Pulldown
907.description: Pull down lever handles toward sides until elbows are to sides. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

908.name: alternative machine
908.description: Pull down lever handles toward sides until elbows are to sides. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

909.name: Gripless Shrug
909.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

910.name: Seated Shrug
910.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

911.name: Shrug
911.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

912.name: Barbell Machine
912.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

913.name: Narrow Grip
913.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

915.name: Shoulder Internal Rotation
915.description: Pull lever arms upward and toward each side of torso as far as possible by simultaneously rotating upper arms. Lower lever arms to original position and repeat.

917.name: Barbell Machine
917.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

918.name: Chest Dip
918.description: Push lever down with elbows away from body. Return until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

919.name: Chest Press
919.description: Press levers until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

920.name: Decline Chest Press
920.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

921.name: alternative machine
921.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

922.name: Wide Grip Chest Press
922.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

923.name: Incline Bench Press
923.description: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Lower weight toward upper chest. Repeat.

924.name: Barbell Machine
924.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

925.name: Parallel Grip
925.description: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Lower weight toward upper chest. Repeat.

926.name: Incline Chest Press
926.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

927.name: on Military Press Machine
927.description: Press levers until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched with elbows positioned out to sides. Repeat.

928.name: Incline Shoulder Raise
928.description: Raise shoulders toward lever grips as far as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

929.name: Lying Crunch
929.description: With hips stationary, raise upper back pad by flexing waist. Return and repeat.

931.name: Seated Leg Raise Crunch
931.description: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up by flexing waist and pelvis. Return and repeat.

933.name: Seated Twisting Leg Raise Crunch
933.description: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up and over to one side by flexing and twisting waist and pelvis. Return and repeat movement to opposite side. Continue alternating between sides.

934.name: Barbell Machine Side Bend
934.description: Bend waist to opposite side of bar. Lower weight by bending toward side with bar and repeat. Continue with opposite side facing opposite direction.

935.name: Seated Twisting Leg Raise Crunch
935.description: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up and over to one side by flexing and twisting waist and pelvis. Return and repeat movement to opposite side. Continue alternating between sides.

936.name: Seated Side Leg Raise Crunch
936.description: Pull handles down while pulling lower leg bar up by flexing waist and pelvis. Return and repeat. Turn seat to opposite side and repeat.

937.name: One Arm Jam
937.description: Push handles out and up while turning torso forward.

938.name: Power Twist
938.description: Move end of barbell upward, across, and downward to opposite side while shifting stance to opposite orientation by pivoting on forefeet and planting new forward foot.

939.name: Push Pull
939.description: Pull forward lever back while pushing other lever forward.

940.name: Deadlift
940.description: Lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

941.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
941.description: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

942.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
942.description: With knees straight, bow forward by bending hips. Bend waist as stirrups approach lowest position. Lift lever by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

943.name: Bent-over Glute Kickback
943.description: Push platform back by extending leg back. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

944.name: Deadlift
944.description: Lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return weight by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Repeat.

945.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
945.description: Bow forward by bending hips. Bend knees slightly during descent and keep waist straight, flexing low back at bottom. With knees slightly bent, raise torso by extending at waist, then hips, gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

946.name: Straight-back
946.description: With back straight, bow forward by bending hips and bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso by extending hips while gradually extending knees until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

947.name: Hip Thrust
947.description: Raise weight upward by extending hips until straight. Lower and repeat.

948.name: on lying leg curl machine
948.description: Raise padded roller upward by extending hips until straight. Lower and repeat.

949.name: 45° Leg Press
949.description: Flex hips and knees to lower lever until hips are completely flexed. Push platform by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

950.name: Single Leg
950.description: Lower platform by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

951.name: Hack Press
951.description: Lower seat by flex hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise seat by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

952.name: Lying Leg Press
952.description: Push lever platform away by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Return lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

953.name: custom-made
953.description: Push lever platform by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Lower lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Repeat.

954.name: Single Leg
954.description: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

955.name: Seated Leg Press
955.description: Push platform(s) away by extending knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

956.name: Alternating
956.description: Push one platform away by extending knee and hip. Return to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

958.name: Lying Hip Extension
958.description: Extend hips and knees until legs are straight. Return to original position by flexing hips and knees. Repeat.

959.name: Power Runner
959.description: Push forward pedal back by extending leg while allowing other pedal to come forward by bending opposite leg. Continue pedalling by alternating between sides.

960.name: Rear Lunge
960.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg   until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

961.name: Barbell Machine
961.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

962.name: Reverse Hyper-extension
962.description: Raise lever by extending hips as high as possible with legs nearly straight. Lower legs to original position. Repeat.

963.name: Single Leg Split Squat
963.description: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

964.name: Barbell Machine
964.description: Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

965.name: Single Leg Squat
965.description: Bend knee forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knee pointed same direction of foot. Squat down as low as possible. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

966.name: Split Squat
966.description: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

967.name: Barbell Machine
967.description: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

968.name: Sliding
968.description: Lower lever downward by sliding platform back and squatting down on forward leg. Keep chest high as hips descend to knee height. Lift sliding forward and extending hips and knee to full extension. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

969.name: Squat
969.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend by bending knees and hip until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

970.name: alternative machine
970.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend by bending knees and hip until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

971.name: Barbell Machine
971.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

972.name: Front Squat
972.description: Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

973.name: Full Squat
973.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

974.name: Hack Squat
974.description: Lower lever by bending hips and knees, until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

975.name: V-Squat
975.description: Bend knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until hips are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

976.name: Seated Hip Abduction
976.description: Move legs away from one another as far as possible. Return and repeat.

977.name: Seated Hip Abduction
977.description: Move legs away from one another as far as possible. Return and repeat.

978.name: Leg Extension
978.description: Move lever forward and upward by extending knees until legs are straight. Return lever to original position by bending knees. Repeat.

979.name: Alternating
979.description: Move one lever forward and upward by extending one knee until leg is straight. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite side. Continue to alternate between sides.

980.name: 45° Leg Press
980.description: Lower platform by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

981.name: Single Leg
981.description: Lower platform by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

982.name: Hack Press
982.description: Lower seat by flexing hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise seat by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

983.name: Lying Leg Press
983.description: Push lever platform away by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Return lever platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

984.name: custom-made
984.description: Push lever platform by extending hips and knees until knees are straight. Flex hips and knees to descend until knees are just short of complete flexion. Repeat.

985.name: Single Leg
985.description: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

986.name: Seated Leg Press
986.description: Push platform(s) away by extending knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

987.name: Alternating
987.description: Push one platform away by extending knee and hip. Return to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

988.name: Single Leg
988.description: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

989.name: Lever Single Leg Standing Leg Press
989.description: Push platform down by extending hip and knee until straight. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

990.name: Rear Lunge
990.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting   leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

991.name: Barbell Machine
991.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

992.name: Single Leg Split Squat
992.description: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

993.name: Barbell Machine
993.description: Lower body on leg by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

994.name: Single Leg Squat
994.description: Bend knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Squat down as low as possible. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

995.name: Split Squat
995.description: With chest high, lift lever by extending hips and knees to full extension. Return until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

996.name: Barbell Machine
996.description: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

997.name: Squat
997.description: Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

998.name: alternative machine
998.description: Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

999.name: Barbell Machine
999.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1000.name: Front Squat
1000.description: Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

1001.name: Full Squat
1001.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees and hips are fully bent. Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Repeat.

1002.name: Hack Squat
1002.description: Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1003.name: V-Squat
1003.description: Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1004.description: Raise one lever pad to back of thigh by flexing knee. Lower lever pad until knee is straight. Raise and lower other leg pad. Continue by alternating legs.

1005.name: Alternating lying leg curl
1005.description: Raise one lever pad to back of thigh by flexing knee. Lower lever pad until knee is straight. Raise and lower other leg pad. Continue by alternating legs.

1006.name: alternative machine
1006.description: Raise lever pad to back of thigh by flexing knee. Lower lever pad until knee is straight. Raise and lower lever pad with opposite leg. Continue by alternating legs.

1007.name: Kneeling Leg Curl
1007.description: Raise ankle to back of thigh by flexing knee. Lower ankle until knee is straight. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1008.name: Lying Leg Curl
1008.description: Raise lever pad to back of thighs by flexing knees. Lower lever pads until knees are straight. Repeat.

1009.name: alternative machine
1009.description: Raise lever pad to back of thighs by flexing knees. Lower lever pads until knees are straight. Repeat.

1010.name: on Reverse Hyper-extension Machine
1010.description: Raise lever back and up by flexing knees. Lower lever until knees are straight. Repeat.

1011.name: Seated Leg Curl
1011.description: Pull lever to back of thighs by flexing knees. Return lever until knees are straight. Repeat.

1012.name: Single Leg
1012.description: Pull padded lever to back of thighs as far as possible by flexing knee. Return padded lever until knee is straight. Change legs and repeat for opposite leg.

1013.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
1013.description: With knees straight, bow forward by bending hips. Bend waist as stirrups approach lowest position. Lift lever by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

1014.name: Straight-back
1014.description: With knees and back straight, bow forward by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Raise body upright by extending hips until standing. Pull shoulders back slightly at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

1015.name: Seated Hip Adduction
1015.description: Move legs together until leg levers make contact. Allow legs to seperate far apart until slight stretch and repeat.

1016.name: 45° Calf Press
1016.description: Push platform by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1017.name: 45° Calf Raise
1017.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1018.name: Calf Extension
1018.description: Push lever by extending ankle as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1019.name: Donkey Calf Raise
1019.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1020.name: Seated Calf Press
1020.description: Push lever platform(s) by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1021.name: Standing Calf Raise
1021.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1022.name: on V-Squat Machine
1022.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1023.name: Seated Calf Raise
1023.description: Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Repeat.

1024.name: 45° Reverse Calf Press
1024.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1025.name: 45° Reverse Calf Raise
1025.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up and back toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet return to platform. Repeat.

1026.name: Reverse Calf Raise
1026.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1027.name: on V-Squat Machine
1027.description: Pull forefeet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1028.name: Reverse Calf Extension
1028.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1029.name: Seated Tibia Raise
1029.description: Lift forefeet upward as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1030.name: Single Leg
1030.description: Lift forefoot upward as far as possible. Return by extending foot until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1031.name: Standing Tibia Raise
1031.description: Lift forefoot upward as far as possible. Return by extending foot until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1032.name: Neck Flexion
1032.description: Move head forward by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return head by hyperextending neck and repeat.

1035.name: Front Raise
1035.description: Raise lever handle forward and upward until upper arm is well above horizontal. Lower and repeat. Repeat with opposite arm.

1036.name: Reclined Shoulder Press
1036.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Lower and repeat.

1037.name: Parallel Grip
1037.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Lower and repeat.

1038.name: Shoulder Press
1038.description: Press lever upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

1039.name: Parallel Grip
1039.description: Press lever upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

1040.name: Alternating
1040.description: Press one lever upward until arm is extended overhead. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue by alternating movement between arms.

1041.name: Lateral Raise
1041.description: Raise arms to sides until upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

1042.name: Extended Arm
1042.description: Raise lever handles to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

1043.name: Kneeling
1043.description: Raise lever handles to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

1044.name: other machine
1044.description: Raise arms to sides until upper arms are horizontal. Return and repeat.

1045.name: Lying Rear Lateral Raise
1045.description: Pull arms up until elbows are beyond back. Lower and repeat.

1046.name: on Lateral Raise Machine
1046.description: Maintaining torso position, raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

1047.name: on Extended Arm Kneeling Lateral Raise Machine
1047.description: Maintaining torso position, raise handles to sides until upper arm is shoulder height. Lower and repeat.

1048.name: Seated Rear Delt Row
1048.description: Pull lever with elbows up out to sides until upper arms are just beyond parallel, keeping upper arm horizontal, perpendicular to torso. Return and repeat.

1049.name: Seated Reverse Fly
1049.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull handles apart and to rear until elbows are just behind back. Return and repeat.

1050.name: gripless
1050.description: Pull arms apart and back until elbows are slightly beyond back. Return to starting position and repeat.

1051.name: on pec deck
1051.description: Pull arms back until elbows are beyond back. Return and repeat.

1052.name: overhand grip
1052.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull handles apart and to rear until elbows are just behind back Return and repeat.

1053.name: pronated grip
1053.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, pull handles apart and to rear until elbows are just behind back. Return and repeat.

1054.name: Incline Triceps Extension
1054.description: Push lever handles up over head until arms are fully extended. Return and repeat.

1055.name: Overhead Triceps Extension
1055.description: Push lever handles up over head until arms are fully extended. Return and repeat.

1056.name: Pushdown
1056.description: Push lever down beyond hips until arm is fully extended. Return and repeat.

1057.name: Seated Close Grip Press
1057.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until forearm is against upper arm. Repeat.

1058.name: Incline Bench
1058.description: Press lever until arms are ext   ended. Return weight until wrists are at side of chest. Repeat.

1059.name: Triceps Dip
1059.description: Push levers down by straightening arms downward. Allow lever bar to raise with elbows pointing back until shoulders are slightly stretched. Repeat.

1060.name: alternative machine
1060.description: Push levers down by straightening arms downward. Allow lever bar to raise with elbows pointing back until shoulders are slightly stretched. Repeat.

1061.name: Overhand Grip
1061.description: Push levers down by straightening arms downward. Allow lever bar to raise with elbows pointing back until shoulders are slightly stretched. Repeat.

1062.name: Triceps Extension
1062.description: Push lever down until arms are fully extended. Return until forearms contact upper arms. Repeat.

1063.name: on other machine
1063.description: Push the lever down until arms are fully extended. Return until forearms contact upper arms. Repeat.

1064.name: Alternating
1064.description: Push one lever out and down until arm is fully extended. Return until forearm contacts upper arm. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue alternating movement between arms.

1065.name: Curl
1065.description: Raise lever handles until elbows are fully flexed with back of upper arm remaining on pad. Lower handles until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

1066.name: Alternating
1066.description: Raise lever on handle until elbow is fully flexed with back of upper arm remaining on pad. Lower handle until arm is fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue to alternate movement between sides.

1067.name: Preacher Curl
1067.description: Raise lever handles toward shoulders. Lower handles until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

1068.name: arms high
1068.description: Pull lever handles toward shoulders. Return handles until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

1069.name: Alternating
1069.description: Pull one lever handle toward shoulder. Return handle until arm is fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue alternating movement between arms.

1070.name: Standing
1070.description: Raise lever handles toward shoulders. Lower handles until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

1071.name: Hammer Preacher Curl
1071.description: Raise lever handles toward shoulders, maintaining palms in grip. Lower handles until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

1072.name: Reverse Curl
1072.description: Raise lever handles until elbows are fully flexed with back of upper arm remaining on pad. Lower handles until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

1073.name: Reverse Preacher Curl
1073.description: Raise lever handles toward shoulders. Lower handles until arm is fully extended. Repeat.

1074.name: Grip
1074.description: Squeeze bars together with both hands until lever makes contact with stationary bars. Lower to original position and repeat.

1076.name: Wrist Curl
1076.description: Raise handles up until wrist is fully flexed. Lower handles until wrists are full hyperextended. Repeat.

1079.name: Radial Deviation
1079.description: Bend wrist so thumb side of fist is pulled up. Return to starting position and repeat.

1080.name: Reverse Wrist Curl
1080.description: Raise handles until wrist is fully hyperextended. Lower handles until wrists are fully flexed. Repeat.

1082.name: Radial Deviation
1082.description: With left hand gripping knob, relax grip of right hand and slide grip downward so fingers are under bottom of knob (by ulnar deviation) and regrip. Relax grip of left hand and rotate knob with right hand so thumb travels closer to body (by radial deviation). Repeat sequence with opposite hands, alternating back and forth until weight plate has raised up near hands. Lower weight steadily with opposite movement or loosen grip slightly to control descent of weight stack.

1083.name: Seated Pronation
1083.description: Rotate shafts by turning palm downward. Return and repeat.

1084.name: Standing Pronation
1084.description: Rotate shaft by turning palm downward. Return and repeat.

1085.name: Seated Supination
1085.description: Rotate shafts by turning palm upward. Return and repeat.

1086.name: Standing Supination
1086.description: Rotate shaft by turning palm upward. Return and repeat.

1087.name: Seated High Row
1087.description: Pull lever back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1088.name: Alternating
1088.description: Pull one lever handle back until elbow is behind back and shoulder is pulled back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

1089.name: Alternative Machine
1089.description: Pull lever down while leaning back slightly. As elbows travel to sides, lift chest slightly and pull shoulders and elbows back. Return until arms are extended and body and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1090.name: Seated Row
1090.description: Pull lever back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1091.name: Wide Grip
1091.description: Pull lever back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1092.name: Seated Row (no chest pad)
1092.description: Pull handles to waist while straightening torso upright. Pull shoulders back and push chest forward while arching back. Return until arms are extended, shoulders are stretched forward, and lower back is flexed forward. Repeat.

1094.name: Underhand Seated Row
1094.description: Pull lever handles back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1095.name: alternative machine
1095.description: Pull levers back until elbows are behind back and shoulders are pulled back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1096.name: Alternating
1096.description: Pull one lever handle back until elbow is behind back and shoulder is pulled back. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched forward. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

1097.name: Close Grip Pulldown
1097.description: Pull down handles to sides of chest while leaning back slightly. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1098.name: alternative machine
1098.description: Pull down handles to sides of chest while leaning back slightly. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1099.name: Front Pulldown
1099.description: Pull down lever to upper chest. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1100.name: Iron Cross
1100.description: With arms straight, pull lever handles down below hips. Return lever handles upward just above shoulder high, or just before slight pressure in shoulder is felt. Repeat.

1101.name: Pulldown
1101.description: Pull levers down to sides of shoulders. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1102.name: alternative machine
1102.description: Pull levers down to sides of shoulders. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1103.name: Parallel Grip
1103.description: Pull levers down to sides of shoulders. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1104.name: Pullover
1104.description: Pull lever forward and down until elbows are to sides. Return until shoulders are fully flexed, or upper arms are parallel to torso. Repeat.

1105.name: Underhand Pulldown
1105.description: Pull down lever handles to sides until elbows are to sides. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1106.name: alternative machine
1106.description: Pull down lever handles to upper chest until elbows are to sides. Return until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1107.name: Alternating
1107.description: Pull down one lever handle to side until elbow is down to side. Return until arm and shoulder are fully extended. Repeat with opposite arm. Continue to alternate pulldown between arms.

1108.name: Gripless Shrug
1108.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

1110.name: Shrug
1110.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

1111.name: Shoulder External Rotation
1111.description: Pull lever away from body. Return and repeat. Adjust lever to opposite side and repeat with other arm.

1112.name: Upright Shoulder External Rotation
1112.description: Pull lever handle upward and back as far as possible by rotating upper arm. Lower lever to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1113.name: Shoulder Internal Rotation
1113.description: Pull lever toward from body. Return and repeat. Adjust lever to opposite side and repeat with other arm.

1114.name: Upright Shoulder Internal Rotation
1114.description: Pull lever handle forward and downward as far as possible by rotating upper arm. Allow lever to return to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1115.name: Chest Dip
1115.description: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

1116.name: alternative machine
1116.description: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

1117.name: Bent-over Fly (iron cross)
1117.description: Bring lever handles together in hugging motion with elbows in fixed position. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

1118.name: Decline Fly
1118.description: Bring padded levers together by pushing pads forward and downward in hugging motion. Return to starting position until chests muscle are stretched. Repeat.

1119.name: Lying Fly
1119.description: Bring padded levers upward and together in hugging motion. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

1120.name: Pec Deck Fly
1120.description: Push levers together. Return until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

1121.name: Decline
1121.description: Push levers together. Return until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

1122.name: Seated Fly
1122.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, push lever handles forward and together. Return to back toward original position until mild stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

1123.name: alternative machine
1123.description: Keeping elbows pointed high, push lever handles forward and together. Return to back toward original position until mild stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

1124.name: gripless
1124.description: Bring padded levers forward and together in hugging motion. Return to starting position until stretch in chests or shoulder is felt. Repeat.

1125.name: Seated Iron Cross
1125.description: Push levers downward and together in hugging motion. Keep shoulders internally rotated so elbows are pointed slightly upward at top and out to sides at bottom. Return to starting position until chest muscles are stretched. Repeat.

1126.name: Bench Press
1126.description: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to upp   er chest. Repeat.

1127.name: Chest Press
1127.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

1128.name: Alternating
1128.description: Press one lever until arm is extended. Return lever back until chest muscle is slightly stretched. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

1129.name: alternative machine
1129.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

1130.name: Parallel Grip
1130.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until shoulders or chest feels slightly stretched. Repeat.

1131.name: Decline Chest Press
1131.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until chest muscles are slightly stretched. Repeat.

1132.name: alternating
1132.description: Press one lever until arm is extended. Return lever back until chest muscle is slightly stretched. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

1133.name: Decline Bench Press
1133.description: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to chest. Repeat.

1134.name: Incline Bench Press
1134.description: Press bar until arms are extended. Lower weight to upper chest. Repeat.

1135.name: Parallel Grip
1135.description: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Lower weight toward upper chest. Repeat.

1136.name: Incline Chest Press
1136.description: Press lever until arms are extended. Return weight until shoulders or chest feels slightly stretched. Repeat.

1137.name: Alternating
1137.description: Press one lever until arm is extended. Return lever back down until chest muscle is slightly stretched. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating between sides.

1138.name: Parallel Grip
1138.description: Press lever bars up until arms are extended. Return weight until shoulders or chest feels slightly stretched. Repeat.

1139.name: Incline Fly
1139.description: Raise lever upward and together in hugging motion. Lower weight until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

1140.name: Chest Dip
1140.description: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

1141.name: Incline Shoulder Raise
1141.description: Raise shoulders toward lever grips as far as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

1142.name: Lying Crunch
1142.description: With hips stationary, raise upper back pad by flexing waist. Return and repeat.

1144.name: Push Crunch
1144.description: Push resistance lever forward by flexing waist. Return by allowing upper body to be pushed back until low back is hyperextended. Repeat.

1145.name: Seated Crunch
1145.description: With hips stationary, flex waist so elbows travel downward. Return and repeat.

1146.name: Arm Bar
1146.description: With hips stationary, flex waist so arms and upper torso travel forward and downward. Return and repeat.

1147.name: Arm Pad
1147.description: With hips stationary, flex waist in "C" shape so elbows point downward. Return and repeat.

1148.name: Chest Pad
1148.description: With hips stationary, flex waist in "C" shape so shoulders travel forward and downward. Return and repeat.

1151.name: Kneeling Twist
1151.description: Rotate lower body through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

1152.name: Lying Twist
1152.description: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Readjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

1153.name: Seated Side Bend
1153.description: With hips stationary, push down lever by bending to side so elbow points downward. Return and repeat. Position lower body to opposite side and repeat.

1154.name: Seated Twist
1154.description: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

1155.name: lower body
1155.description: Rotate lower body through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

1156.name: arms up
1156.description: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

1157.name: gripless
1157.description: Rotate torso through waist to opposite side. Return and repeat. Adjust range of motion setting to opposite side and repeat in opposite direction.

1158.name: Side Crunch
1158.description: With hips stationary, flex waist in "C" shape so elbows point downward. Return and repeat. Position lower body to opposite side and repeat.

1159.name: Standing Side Bend
1159.description: Bend waist to opposite side of lever. Lower weight by bending to opposite side and repeat. Continue with opposite side facing opposite direction.

1160.name: Back Extension
1160.description: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

1161.name: on older machine
1161.description: Extend lower hips and low back until extended. Return and repeat.

1162.name: on rehab machine
1162.description: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

1163.name: Kneeling Back Extension
1163.description: Extend spine until hyperextended. Return and repeat.

1164.name: Pull Back Extension
1164.description: Pull lever back until spine hyperextends while keeping hips pushed back against pad. Return and repeat.

1165.name: Bent-over
1165.description: Push foot lever back by extending hip. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Reposition and continue with opposite leg.

1166.name: Kneeling
1166.description: Keeping one leg on shin pad, extend hip of other leg and push roller pad back. Raise roller pad up until hip is completely extended. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1167.name: Alternating
1167.description: Keeping one leg on shin pad, extending hip of other leg and push roller pad back. Raise roller pad up until hip is completely extended. Return leg to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue alternating between each side.

1168.name: Lying
1168.description: Push padded leg bar down until hips are extended. Return and repeat.

1170.name: Standing
1170.description: Lower lever by extending hip. Return until knee is higher than hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1171.name: alternative machine
1171.description: Extend lever back by extending hip and straightening leg. Return by flexing hip and knee. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1172.name: Alternating Lying Leg Press
1172.description: Lower one lever platform toward body by bending knee and hip until weight taps or nearly taps unused portion of weight stack. Push lever platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

1173.name: Seated Leg Press
1173.description: Extend knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

1174.name: Single Leg
1174.description: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1175.name: Bent-over
1175.description: Push platform or pedal back by extending leg. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1176.name: Kneeling
1176.description: Push platform back by extending leg back. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1177.name: Standing
1177.description: Push platform down by extending leg until straight. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

1178.name: Squat
1178.description: Raise lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

1179.name: V-Squat
1179.description: Raise lever by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down with knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees or hips are near complete flexion. Repeat.

1180.name: Split
1180.description: Squat down with knee pointed same direction as foot. Allow leg to bend behind with forefoot on floor. Descend until forward hip is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hip until leg is straight. Repeat. Continue with other leg.

1181.name: Single Leg Split
1181.description: Raise lever by extending knees and hips. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

1182.name: Alternating
1182.description: Transfer right foot back to inside of rear vertical platform. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Raise lever by extending knees and hips until knee is straight. Return right foot to original position by other foot. Repeat with opposite leg movement and continue alternating between sides.

1183.name: Kneeling Hip Internal Rotation (on hip abduction machine)
1183.description: Pull levers apart as far as possible with legs by externally rotating hips. Return until feet make contact, then repeat.

1184.name: Lying Hip Abduction
1184.description: Move legs away from one another by abduction hip. Return and repeat.

1185.name: Seated Hip Abduction
1185.description: Move legs apart as far as possible. Return and repeat.

1186.name: Standing Hip Abduction
1186.description: Raise leg against roller pad to side by abduction hip. Return and repeat. Reposition roller pad lever and continue with opposite leg.

1187.name: Seated Hip Abduction
1187.description: Move legs apart as far as possible. Return and repeat.

1188.name: Leg Extension
1188.description: Move lever forward and upward by extending knees until legs are straight. Return lever to original position by bending knees. Repeat.

1189.name: Alternating
1189.description: Move lever forward and upward by extending one knee until leg is straight. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue to alternate between sides.

1190.name: Unilateral Machine
1190.description: Move one lever forward and upward by extending one knee until leg is straight. Lower to original position. Repeat with opposite side. Continue to alternate between sides.

1191.name: Alternating Lying Leg Press
1191.description: Lower one lever platform toward body by bending knee and hip until weight taps or nearly taps unused portion of weight stack. Push lever platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

1192.name: Seated Leg Press
1192.description: Push platform away by extending knees and hips. Return and repeat.

1193.name: Single Leg
1193.description: Push platform away by extending hip and knee. Return by bending leg until knee or hip is just short of complete flexion. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1194.name: Squat
1194.description: Lift lever up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Lower lever by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

1195.name: V-Squat
1195.description: Raise sled by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Squat down with knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until knees or hips are near complete flexion. Repeat.

1196.name: Split
1196.description: Squat down with knee pointed same direction as foot. Allow leg to bend behind with forefoot on floor. Descend until forward hip is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hip until leg is straight. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1197.name: Single Leg Split
1197.description: Raise lever by extending knees and hips. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positions.

1198.name: Alternating
1198.description: Transfer right foot back to inside of rear vertical platform. Lower lever by flexing hips and knees until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Raise lever by extending knees and hips until knee is straight. Return right foot to original position by other foot. Repeat with opposite leg movement and continue alternating between sides.

1199.name: Bent-over Leg Curl
1199.description: Raise lever up by bending knee as high as possible. Return lever until knee is straight. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1200.name: Alternating
1200.description: Raise left foot slightly off of floor or platform. Raise lever up with left leg, bending knee as high as possible. Return lever until knee is straight. Shift body weight to left foot and raise right foot slightly off of floor or platform. Raise lever up with right leg, bending knee as high as possible. Continue alternating movement between legs.

1201.name: Kneeling Leg Curl
1201.description: Raise ankle to back of thigh by flexing knee. Lower ankle until knee is straight. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1202.name: Lying Leg Curl
1202.description: Raise lever pad to back of thighs by flexing knees. Lower lever pads until knees are straight. Repeat.

1203.name: Alternating
1203.description: Raise lever pad to back of thighs by flexing one knee. Lower lever pads until knee is straight and repeat with opposite leg. Continue to alternate between sides.

1204.name: Seated Leg Curl
1204.description: Pull far padded lever toward back of thighs by flexing knees. Return lever until knees are straight. Repeat.

1205.name: Single Leg
1205.description: Pull far padded lever toward back of thighs as far as possible by flexing knee. Return padded lever until knee is straight. Change legs and repeat for opposite leg.

1206.name: Standing Leg Curl
1206.description: Pull lever up to back of thigh by flexing knee. Return lever until knee is straight. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1207.name: Alternating
1207.description: Raise left foot slightly off of floor or platform. Raise lever up with left leg, bending knee as high as possible. Return lever until knee is straight. Shift body weight to left foot and raise right foot slightly off of floor or platform. Raise lever up with right leg, bending knee as high as possible. Continue alternating movement between legs.

1208.name: on Leg Extension Machine
1208.description: Pull lever to back of thigh by flexing knee. Return lever until knee is straight. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1209.name: on Multi-hip Machine
1209.description: Pull padded roller to glutes by flexing knee. Lower padded roller until knee is straight. Repeat. Reposition roller pad lever and continue with opposite leg.

1210.name: Straight Leg Lying Hip Extension
1210.description: With knees straight, extend lever downward until hips are extended. Return lever to upright position without allowing back of hips to raise up off of bench. Repeat.

1211.name: Lying Hip Adduction
1211.description: Move legs together. Return and repeat.

1212.name: Seated Hip Adduction
1212.description: Move legs together. Return and repeat.

1213.name: Standing Hip Adduction
1213.description: Move leg toward and across supporting leg Return and repeat. Reposition roller pad lever and continue with opposite leg.

1214.name: 45° Calf Raise
1214.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1215.name: Calf Extension
1215.description: Push lever by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1216.name: Bilateral
1216.description: Push lever by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1217.name: Alternating
1217.description: Push left pedal by extending ankle as far as possible while allowing right pedal to return back until calf is stretched. Reverse motion by pushing right pedal and allowing left pedal to return back. Continue to alternate motion.

1218.name: Donkey Calf Raise
1218.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1219.name: Seated Calf Press
1219.description: Push lever by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1220.name: Standing Calf Raise
1220.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1221.name: belt loaded
1221.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1222.name: Forward Angled
1222.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1223.name: Bent-knee Calf Extension
1223.description: Push lever by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1224.name: Alternating
1224.description: Push left pedal by extending ankle knee Simultaneously allow right pedal to return back by relaxing ankle and bending knee more. Reverse motion by pushing right pedal and allowing left pedal to return back by same means. Continue to alternate motion.

1225.name: Seated Calf Raise
1225.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1226.name: Seated Calf Extension
1226.description: Push lever platform down by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1227.name: Donkey Reverse Calf Raise
1227.description: Pull forefoot up and toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed away from body. Repeat.

1228.name: Reverse Calf Extension
1228.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1229.name: Reverse Calf Raise
1229.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1230.name: Seated Reverse Calf Press
1230.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1231.name: Lying Neck Flexion
1231.description: Move head up by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return by hyperextending neck and repeat.

1232.name: Neck Flexion
1232.description: Move head up by flexing neck until chin touches upper chest. Return by hyperextending neck and repeat.

1233.name: Lateral Neck Flexion
1233.description: Move head up to side by laterally flexing neck. Lower head to opposite side and repeat. Lie on other side and continue.

1234.name: Lying Neck Extension
1234.description: Move head up by hyperextending neck up as high as possible. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

1235.name: Neck Extension
1235.description: Move head up by hyperextending neck up as high as possible. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

1236.name: Seated Neck Extension
1236.description: Move head up by hyperextending neck up as high as possible. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

1237.name: Harness
1237.description: Move head up by hyperextending neck. Return by bending neck down until chin touches upper chest. Repeat.

1238.name: Bench Dip
1238.description: Lower body by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder, or rear end touches floor. Raise body and repeat.

1239.name: Close Grip Push-up
1239.description: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

1240.name: Triceps Dip
1240.description: Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1242.name: Chin-up
1242.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1243.name: Neutral Grip
