1243.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1244.name: Parallel Close Grip Pull-up
1244.description: Pull body up until elbow are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1245.name: Pull-up
1245.description: Pull body up until chin is above bar. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1246.name: neutral grip
1246.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1247.name: open-centered bar
1247.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1248.name: Rear Pull-up
1248.description: Pull body up until bar touches back of neck. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1249.name: Chest Dip
1249.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1250.name: Push-up
1250.description: Keeping body straight, lower body to floor by bending arms. Push body up until arms are extended. Repeat.

1251.name: on handles
1251.description: Keeping body ridged, lower body downward by bending arms until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders. Push body back up until arms are extended. Repeat.

1252.name: Chest Dip
1252.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1253.name: Crunch
1253.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

1254.name: arms crossed
1254.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso from mat. Keep low back on mat and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact mat. Repeat.

1255.name: on ball
1255.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

1256.name: Overhead
1256.description: Keeping arms extended and medicine ball over upper chest, flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position. Repeat.

1257.name: Incline Crunch
1257.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

1258.name: arms crossed
1258.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench. Keep low back on bench and raise torso up as high as possible. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

1259.name: Incline Sit-up
1259.description: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

1260.name: arms crossed
1260.description: Raise torso from bench by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat.

1261.name: Medicine Ball Overhead Throw Sit-up (machine)
1261.description: With ball in both hands, lie down onto back support while lowering medicine ball behind head. Raise torso from back support by bending waist and hips while raising ball overhead. Immediately throw ball into target and grasp other medicine ball at bottom of chute. Repeat movement.

1262.name: Chest Throw Sit-up
1262.description: With ball in both hands, lie down onto back support while lowering medicine ball to chest. Raise torso from back support by bending waist and hips while pushing ball away from chest. Immediately throw ball into target and grasp other medicine ball at bottom of chute. Repeat movement.

1263.name: Sit-up
1263.description: Raise torso from floor by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact with floor or mat. Repeat.

1264.name: arms crossed
1264.description: Raise torso from floor by bending waist and hips. Return until back of shoulders contact with floor or mat. Repeat.

1265.name: Hanging Leg-Hip Raise
1265.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

1266.name: Incline Leg-Hip Raise
1266.description: Raise legs by flexing hips while flexing knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist, raising hips from board. Return until waist, hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1269.name: Bosu support
1269.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees. As hips approach full flexion, lean back. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist and raising hips and low back from convexed surface. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

1270.name: on parallel bars
1270.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended. Repeat.

1271.name: V-up
1271.description: While keeping feet together, simultaneously raise straight legs and torso. Reach toward raised feet. Return to starting position. Repeat.

1272.name: Incline Twisting Crunch
1272.description: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from bench to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1273.name: Side Crunch
1273.description: Flex waist, raising upper torso off surface. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat and continue with movement in opposite position.

1274.name: on ball
1274.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat. Position legs in opposite position and continue.

1275.name: Twisting Crunch
1275.description: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso off surface to one side. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1276.name: on ball
1276.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat.

1277.name: Incline Twisting Sit-up
1277.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side, alternating twists.

1278.name: arms crossed
1278.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1279.name: Twisting Sit-up
1279.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1280.name: arms crossed
1280.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1281.name: Lying Twist
1281.description: Lower legs to one side until side of thigh is on floor. Raise and lower legs to opposite side. Repeat.

1282.name: Bent-knee
1282.description: Lower legs to one side until side of thigh is on floor. Raise and lower legs to opposite side. Repeat.

1283.name: Russian Twist
1283.description: Turn torso to one side while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Return weight back over shoulders by rotating torso to original position. Continue lowering weight to opposite side. Repeat.

1284.name: Russian Twist (on ball)
1284.description: Turn torso to one side while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Return weight back over shoulders by rotating torso to original position. Continue lowering weight to opposite side. Repeat.

1285.name: 45° Side Bend
1285.description: Raise torso upward by lateral flexing waist. Lower torso by bending waist downward. Repeat. Position body facing opposite side and continue with opposite side.

1286.name: Side Bend on ball
1286.description: Raise side of torso up by laterally flexing waist. Lower torso back on ball and repeat. Position other side on ball and repeat with opposite side.

1287.name: Incline Twisting Crunch
1287.description: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso from bench to one side. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1288.name: Side Crunch
1288.description: Flex waist, raising upper torso off surface. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat and continue with movement in opposite position.

1289.name: on ball
1289.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat. Position legs in opposite position and continue.

1290.name: Twisting Crunch
1290.description: Flex and twist waist to raise upper torso off surface to one side. Return until back of shoulders return to surface. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1291.name: on ball
1291.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso. Return to original position and repeat.

1292.name: Incline Twisting Sit-up
1292.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side, alternating twists.

1293.name: arms crossed
1293.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline board. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1294.name: Twisting Sit-up
1294.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1295.name: arms crossed
1295.description: Flex and twist waist to one direction while raising torso from bench by bending hips. Return until back of shoulders contact floor or mat. Repeat to opposite side alternating twists.

1296.name: Hyperextension
1296.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is vertical. Repeat.

1297.name: Back Extension
1297.description: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise, or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

1298.name: on ball
1298.description: Raise torso off of ball by hyperextending spine. Lower torso onto ball allowing spine to flex. Repeat.

1299.name: Hyperextension (45°)
1299.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until mild stretch is felt or torso is approximately perpendicular to legs. Repeat.

1300.name: Back Extension (45°)
1300.description: Lower body by bending waist until fully flexed. Raise, or extend waist until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

1301.name: Belt Squat
1301.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1302.name: Front Squat
1302.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1303.name: Reverse Hyper-extension
1303.description: Raise weight by extending hips as high as possible until legs are nearly straight. Lower legs to original position. Repeat.

1304.name: Single Leg Squat
1304.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1305.name: Lying Hip Abduction
1305.description: Raise weighted leg up off ground as high as possible. Balance bar on side of foot while holding onto closest side of bar. Return to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1306.name: Decline Sit-up
1306.description: Lower body back until hips are almost extended. Raise body by flexing hips until torso is upright. Repeat.

1307.name: Hanging Leg Raise
1307.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1308.name: Straight Leg
1308.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return until hips are extended downward. Repeat.

1309.name: Incline Leg Raise
1309.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1310.name: arms on pads
1310.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1311.name: Incline Straight Leg Raise
1311.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past perpendicular to torso. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1312.name: arms on pads
1312.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until hips are flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1313.name: Lying Leg Raise
1313.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1314.name: Roman Chair Sit-up
1314.description: Lower body back until hips are almost extended. Raise body by flexing hips until torso is upright. Repeat.

1315.name: Seated Leg Raise
1315.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees while pulling torso slightly forward to maintain balance. Return by extending hips and knees and lean torso back to counter balance. Repeat.

1316.name: Vertical Leg Raise
1316.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed or knees are well above hips. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1317.name: on Parallel Bars
1317.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return until hips and knees are extended. Repeat.

1318.name: Straight Leg
1318.description: With knees straight, raise legs by flexing hips until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return until hips are extended. Repeat.

1319.name: Belt Squat
1319.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Squat up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1320.name: Front Squat
1320.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1321.name: Single Leg Squat
1321.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body   back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1322.name: Sissy Squat
1322.description: With hips and waist straight, bend knees to allow body to fall backwards as knees come forward. Allow heels to raise from floor. Lower body until knees are almost fully flexed or near floor. Return to original position by extending knees as heels return to floor.

1323.name: on apparatus
1323.description: Allow body to fall backwards by bending knees. During descent, gradually bend hips, yet keep chest high and don't allow torso to angle forward. Lower body until back of thigh is against upper pad. Rise to original position by extending knees and hips while keeping shoulders behind hips. Repeat.

1324.name: Glute-Ham Raise
1324.description: From upright position, lower body by straightening knees until body is horizontal. Continue to lower torso by bending hips until body is upside down. Raise torso by extending hips until fully extended. Continue to raise body by flexing knees until body is upright. Repeat.

1325.name: Inverse Leg Curl
1325.description: Lower body until horizontal by straightening knees. Raise body by flexing knees, only allowing hips to bend slightly. Repeat.

1326.name: Hyperextension
1326.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until fully flexed. Repeat.

1327.name: Back Raise
1327.description: Lower body by bending hips until fully flexed. Raise or extend hips until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

1328.name: Hyperextension (45°)
1328.description: Raise upper body until hips and waist are fully extended. Lower body by bending hips and waist until fully flexed. Repeat.

1329.name: Back Raise (45°)
1329.description: Lower body by bending hips until fully flexed. Raise or extend hips until torso is parallel to legs. Repeat.

1330.name: Lying Hip Adduction
1330.description: Raise weighted leg up off floor as high as possible while balanciong bar inside of foot and holding onto nearest side of bar. Return to floor and repeat. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1331.name: Donkey Calf Raise
1331.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1332.name: Single Leg Calf Raise
1332.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Lower heel by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1333.name: Neck Flexion
1333.description: Increase angle of body by bowing head until chin touches upper chest. Lower angle of body by raising head. Repeat.

1334.name: Lateral Neck Flexion
1334.description: Lower angle of body by tilting head to side of suspension trainer. Increase angle of body by tilting head away from side of suspension trainer. Repeat and continue in opposite position.

1335.name: Neck Extension
1335.description: Lower angle of body by bowing head until chin is near upper chest. Increase angle of body by raising head. Repeat.

1336.name: Front Raise
1336.description: Raise arms upward overhead by flexing shoulders with arms straight. Return and lower body back until arms are extended straight forward in original position. Repeat.

1337.name: Y Raise
1337.description: Raise arms upward and outward in shape of a Y while keeping arms straight. Return and lower body back in opposite motion until arms are extended straight forward in original position. Repeat.

1338.name: Rear Delt Row
1338.description: Pull body up while keeping elbows pointed directly out to each side and body and legs straight. Pull until elbows are directly lateral to each side without allowing elbows to drop. Return until arms are extended straight and shoulders are stretched forward, maintaining high elbow position. Repeat.

1339.name: Reverse Fly
1339.description: Pull handles out to sides while keeping stiff elbow position and maintaining shoulder at 90° plane to torso throughout exercise. Raise up until upper arms are in-line to one another. Return to original position in same plane and repeat.

1340.name: Triceps Dip
1340.description: Push body up until arms are straight. Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

1341.name: Self-assisted
1341.description: Lower body by bending arms back. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees to bend, keeping toes in contact with floor. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up back up until arms are straight. Repeat with minimal assistance from legs.

1342.name: Triceps Extension
1342.description: Lower body by bending elbows, allowing head to travel between suspension handles. Raise body up and back up until arms are extended. Repeat.

1343.name: with rope
1343.description: Keeping body straight, raise body up and back up until arms are extended. Lower body by bending elbows, allowing head to travel between ends of rope. Repeat.

1344.name: Arm Curl
1344.description: Bring handles toward shoulders by flexing arms, while keeping elbows pointed forward. Return by straightening arms and repeat.

1345.name: Inverted Row
1345.description: Pull body up so sides of chest make contact with handles while keeping body straight. Return until arms are extended straight and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1346.name: Bent-knee
1346.description: Pull body up so sides of chest make contact with handles while keeping body straight. Return until arms are extended straight and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1347.name: Power Pull
1347.description: Rotate body and extended arm, reaching outward while lowering body downward by extending arm holding onto handle. Extend arms and shoulders in-line with suspension strap so body is angled back to one side. Return by raising body back upward in opposite motion, reaching outward and toward suspension strap while pulling handle back to side of chest until body is upright and arm parallel with angle of strap. Repeat and continue with opposite side.

1348.name: Row
1348.description: Pull body up so sides of chest make contact with handles while keeping body and legs straight. Return until arms are extended straight and shoulders are stretched forward. Repeat.

1349.name: Suspended Rollout
1349.description: Lean body forward while maintaining small bend in hip. Allow arms to bend forward to sides of head. Bend over as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until kneeling upright in original position. Repeat.

1350.name: Inverted Shrug
1350.description: Raise body up a high as possible by pulling shoulders toward ears. Lower body to original position and repeat.

1351.name: Shoulder External Rotation
1351.description: Pull handles apart from each side, while keeping fixed elbow position and body and legs straight throughout movement. Raise forward so handles are to each side of body. Return back until handles come back together in front of body. Repeat.

1352.name: Chest Dip
1352.description: Push body up until arms are straight. Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

1353.name: Assisted
1353.description: Lower body by bending arms back. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees to bend, keeping feet in contact with floor. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up back up until arms are straight. Repeat with minimal assistance from legs.

1354.name: Chest Press
1354.description: Lower body by bending arms while keeping body straight. Allow handles to come apart slightly to keep in-line with elbows flaring out. Stop descent once mild stretch is felt through shoulders or chest. Push body up to original position, allowing handles to travel inward to keep in line with elbows converging until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

1355.name: Fly
1355.description: Lower body by allowing suspension handles to separate outward until mild stretch is felt in chest. Reverse motion by bringing handles back together in hugging motion. Repeat.

1356.name: Jack-knife
1356.description: Pull legs under torso by bending hips and knees. Pull knees toward chest hips and knees until completely flexed. Return by extending hips and knees to original position. Repeat.

1357.name: Jack-knife Pike
1357.description: Pull knees toward shoulders while raising hips very high. Lower hips by extending body to original straight position, while keeping shins close to horizontal. Repeat.

1358.name: Pull Through
1358.description: Pull hips back while flexing spine in C shape. Raise hips up high by straightening spine and hips until straight.

1359.name: Kneeling Rollout
1359.description: Lean body forward while maintaining small bend in hip. Allow arms to bend forward to sides of head. Bend over as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until kneeling upright in original position. Repeat.

1360.name: Standing
1360.description: Lean body forward while extending hips and allowing arms to extend forward to sides of head. Bend over as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until standing while being bent over slightly at hips in original position. Repeat.

1361.name: Hanging Leg Hip Raise
1361.description: Raise legs by flexing hips and knees until hips are fully flexed. Continue to raise knees toward shoulders by flexing waist. Return until waist, hips, and knees are extended downward. Repeat.

1362.name: Pendulum
1362.description: Move both legs to one side then to opposite side by moving through waist and hips. Continue swinging legs side to side.

1363.name: Side Bend
1363.description: Lower hips away from direction of suspension trainer anchor by laterally flexing spine. Return to original upright position and repeat. Reposition body facing opposite direction. Continue with other side.

1364.name: Side Bridge
1364.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Reposition to opposite side and continue.

1365.name: Twist
1365.description: While keeping arms straight and shoulders fixed, rotate torso up to one side. Twist until upright or slight stretch is felt in waist, whichever comes soonest. Rotate back to starting position and repeat. Continue on opposite side.

1366.name: Twisting Jack-knife
1366.description: Pull knees toward one elbow by bending hips a   nd knees to one side. Twist legs to one side, until hips and knees are completely flexed. Return by extending hips and knees to original straight position. Perform movement to opposite side. Continue by alternating each side.

1367.name: Hyperextension
1367.description: Drive hips forward until hips are straight, while keeping arms and shoulders straight. Near top of motion, reach back with arms over head and hyperextend spine. While keeping arms over head, lower body with hips falling back down to starting position and repeat.

1368.name: Pull Through
1368.description: Pull hips back while flexing spine in C shape. Raise hips up high by straightening spine and hips until straight.

1369.name: Hip Bridge
1369.description: Raise hips up by extending hips until fully extended. Lower hips until hips and back make contact with mat. Repeat.

1370.name: Reclining Squat
1370.description: While reclined back and holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward while keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are perpendicular to body's angle of movement. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to reclined standing position with body straight. Repeat.

1371.name: Single Leg Squat
1371.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back, up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1372.name: Single Leg Split Squat
1372.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1373.name: Self-assisted
1373.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting leg. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1374.name: Hip Abduction
1374.description: Pull legs apart as far as possible. Return by placing legs together and repeat.

1375.name: Side Bend
1375.description: Lower hips away from direction of suspension trainer anchor by laterally flexing spine. Return to original upright position and repeat. Reposition body facing opposite direction. Continue with other side.

1376.name: Side Bridge
1376.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Reposition to opposite side and continue.

1377.name: Suspended Twist
1377.description: While keeping arms straight and shoulders fixed, rotate torso up to one side. Twist until upright or slight stretch is felt in waist, whichever comes soonest. Rotate back to starting position and repeat. Continue on opposite side.

1378.name: Mountain Climber
1378.description: Simultaneously alternate leg positions by straightening bent leg behind, while bending straight leg forward. Repeat.

1379.name: Pike
1379.description: Raise rear end up as high as possible by bending hips. Pull feet toward hands, while keeping knees straight. Return by extending hips to original straight body position. Repeat.

1380.name: Reclining Squat
1380.description: While reclined back and holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward while keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are perpendicular to body's angle of movement. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to reclined standing position with body straight. Repeat.

1381.name: Single Leg Squat
1381.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back, up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1382.name: Single Leg Split Squat
1382.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1383.name: Self-assisted
1383.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of supporting leg. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1384.name: Leg Curl
1384.description: Pull heels toward rear end by bending knees and hips simultaneously. Lower body to original position by straightening knees and hips. Repeat.

1385.name: Hamstring Runner
1385.description: Simultaneously alternate leg positions by straightening bent leg while bending straight knee. Repeat.

1386.name: Hanging Leg Curl
1386.description: Pull body toward feet by bending knees and hips. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1387.name: Straight Hip
1387.description: Pull body toward feet by bending knees while keeping hips and back straight. Roll onto feet until knees are fully flexed. Return body to original position by extending knees maintaining straight hip position. Repeat.

1388.name: Hyperextension
1388.description: Drive hips forward until hips are straight, while keeping arms and shoulders straight. Near top of motion, reach back with arms over head and hyperextend spine. While keeping arms over head, lower body with hips falling back down to starting position and repeat.

1389.name: Straight Hip Leg Curl
1389.description: Bend knees, pulling heels toward rear end while keeping hips and low back straight. Raise up until lower legs are vertical or fully flexed. Lower body to original position by straightening knees, maintaining straight hip position. Repeat.

1390.name: Single Leg
1390.description: Bend knee of leg in suspension trainer while keeping other leg extended. Continue pulling heel toward rear end while keeping hips and low back straight. Raise up until lower leg is vertical or fully flexed. Lower body to original position by straightening knee until leg is straight and next to extended leg, maintaining straight hip position throughout movement. Repeat.

1391.name: Side Bend
1391.description: Lower hips away from direction of suspension trainer anchor by laterally flexing spine. Return to original upright position and repeat. Reposition body facing opposite direction. Continue with other side.

1392.name: Side Bridge
1392.description: Raise hips upward by lateral flexion of spine. Lower to original position and repeat. Reposition to opposite side and continue.

1393.name: Single Leg Forward Angled Calf Raise
1393.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Allow body to travel forward and upward in same direction as body is orientated. Lower heel allowing foot to come back down flat on floor. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1396.name: Front Plank
1396.description: Raise body upward by straightening body in straight line. Hold position.

1397.name: Stability Ball Rollout
1397.description: Lean forward and roll ridged arms out over ball. Roll forward as far as possible. Raise body back up by pulling arms back until kneeling upright in original position. Repeat.

1400.name: Rear Bridge
1400.description: Raise hips up off floor until hips are straight. Hold position.

1401.name: Decline Rear Bridge
1401.description: Raise hips up off floor until hips are straight. Hold position.

1402.name: Single Leg
1402.description: While keeping leg straight inline with body, raise hips up off floor until hip of bent leg is straight. Hold position. Change position and repeat hold on opposite side.

1403.name: Incline Rear Bridge
1403.description: Raise hips up off floor until hips are straight. Hold position.

1404.name: Seated DB Shrugs
1404.description:
Sit on a bench with dumbbells in both hands, palms facing your body, back straight.
Elevate your shoulders and hold the contracted position at the apex of the motion.
Slowly lower your shoulders back to starting position.

1405.name: Arnold Press
1405.description: Initiate movement by bringing elbows out to sides. Continue to raise elbows outward while pressing dumbbells overhead until arms are straight. Lower to front of shoulders in opposite pattern and repeat.

1406.name: Front Raise
1406.description: Raise dumbbells forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower and repeat.

1407.name: Alternating
1407.description: Raise one dumbbell forward and upward with palms positioned downward until upper arm is above horizontal. Lower and repeat with opposite arm, alternating between arms.

1408.name: Incline
1408.description: With elbows straight or slightly bent, raise one dumbbell forward, up and over shoulder until upper arm is vertical. Lower dumbbell down to starting position. Repeat raise with other arm, alternating between sides.

1409.name: Seated
1409.description: Raise one dumbbell forward and upward while turning palms downward as soon as dumbbell clears thigh. Continue raising dumbbell until upper arm is above horizontal. Lower and turn palms inward while dumbbells travels past thigh until arm is in original vertical position. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating movement pattern between arms.

1410.name: Full Can
1410.description: Raise one dumbbell forward and upward until upper arm is above horizontal. Lower to original vertical position. Repeat with opposite arm, alternating movement pattern between arms.

1411.name: Seated
1411.description: Raise dumbbells forward and upward while turning palms downward as soon as dumbbells clear thighs. Continue raising dumbbells until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower dumbbells and turn palms inward while dumbbells travels past thighs until arms are in original vertical position. Repeat.

1412.name: Full Can
1412.description: Raise dumbbells forward and upward until upper arms are above horizontal. Lower to original vertical position and repeat.

1413.name: Shoulder Press
1413.description: Press dumbbells upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower to sides of shoulders and repeat.

1414.name: One Arm
1414.description: Press dumbbell upward until arm is extended overhead. Lower to side of shoulder and repeat.

1415.name: Reclined
1415.description: Press dumbbells upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower to sides of upper chest and repeat.

1417.name: Incline Y Raise
1417.description: With elbows slightly bent, raise arms with dumbbells upward and outward to sides in Y configuration until elbows are approximately lateral to each ear. Lower dumbbells in reverse pattern until they are below shoulders and repeat.

1418.name: Lateral Raise
1418.description: Raise upper arms to sides until slightly bent elbows are shoulder height while maintaining elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

1419.name: One Arm
1419.description: Raise upper arm to side until slightly bent elbow is shoulder height while maintaining elbow's height above or equal to wrist. Lower and repeat.

1420.name: Seated
1420.description: Raise upper arm to side until slightly bent elbow is shoulder height while maintaining elbow's height above or equal to wrist. Lower and repeat.

1421.name: Seated
1421.description: Raise upper arms to sides until slightly bent elbows are shoulder height while maintaining elbows' height above or equal to wrists. Lower and repeat.

1422.name: Lying Lateral Raise
1422.description: Raise dumbbell from floor until arm is vertical. Maintain fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat.

1423.name: Raise
1423.description: Pull dumbbells up to sides of ribs with elbows out to sides. Lower and repeat.

1424.name: Upright Row
1424.description: Pull dumbbells to front of shoulder with elbows leading out to sides. Allow wrists to flex as dumbbells rise upward. Lower and repeat.

1425.name: One Arm
1425.description: Pull dumbbell to front of shoulder with elbow leading. Allow wrist to flex as dumbbell rises upward. Lower and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1426.name: Seated
1426.description: Pull dumbbell to front of shoulder with elbow leading out to side. Allow wrists to flex as dumbbell rises upward. Lower and repeat.

1427.name: Lying Rear Delt Row
1427.description: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso and dumbbells just below elbows, pull dumbbells up until elbows are just above shoulders. Return and repeat.

1428.name: Incline
1428.description: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso and dumbbells just below elbows, pull dumbbells up until elbows are just above shoulders. Return and repeat.

1429.name: Lying Rear Lateral Raise
1429.description: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Maintain height of elbows above wrists by raising "pinkie" side up. Lower and repeat.

1430.name: One Arm
1430.description: Raise upper arm to side until elbow is shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso with elbow straight throughout exercise. Maintain palm forward position. Lower and repeat.

1431.name: Rear Lateral Raise
1431.description: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Maintain height of elbows above wrists by raising "pinkie finger" side up. Lower and repeat.

1432.name: Rear Delt Row
1432.description: Pull dumbbell up out to side with upper arm perpendicular to trunk until upper arm is just beyond horizontal. Lower and repeat.

1433.name: Seated Rear Lateral Raise
1433.description: Raise upper arms to sides until elbows are shoulder height. Maintain upper arms perpendicular to torso and fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Maintain elbows height above wrists by raising "pinkie finger" side up. Lower and repeat.

1434.name: Side Lying Rear Delt Raise
1434.description: Raise dumbbell from floor until it travels above shoulder. Return dumbbell to floor at original position. Repeat.

1435.name: Front Lateral Raise
1435.description: Raise arms to side, slightly to front until shoulder height or slightly higher. Lower and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1436.name: Seated
1436.description: Raise arms to side, slightly in front until shoulder height or slightly higher. Lower and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1437.name: Full Can Lateral Raise
1437.description: Raise arms to side with thumb side up. Lower and repeat.

1438.name: Lying Lateral Raise
1438.description: Raise dumbbell from floor until arm is vertical. Maintain fixed elbow position (10° to 30° angle) throughout exercise. Lower and repeat.

1439.name: Bench Press
1439.description: Press dumbbells up with elbows to sides until arms are extended. Lower weight to sides of chest until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

1440.name: Decline Bench Press
1440.description: Press dumbbells up with elbows to sides until arms are extended. Lower weight to sides of chest until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

1441.name: Decline Fly
1441.description: Lower dumbbells to sides until chest muscles are stretched with elbows fixed. Bring dumbbells together in wide hugging motion until dumbbells are nearly together. Repeat.

1442.name: Fly
1442.description: Lower dumbbells to sides until chest muscles are stretched with elbows fixed in slightly bent position. Bring dumbbells together in wide hugging motion until dumbbells are nearly together. Repeat.

1443.name: Pullover
1443.description: Keeping elbows slightly bent throughout movement, lower dumbbell over and beyond head until upper arms are in-line with torso. Pull dumbbell up and over chest. Repeat.

1444.name: on apparatus
1444.description: Keeping elbows slightly bent throughout movement, lower dumbbell over and beyond head until upper arms are in-line with torso. Pull dumbbell up and over chest. Repeat.

1445.name: on arched bench
1445.description: Keeping elbows slightly bent throughout movement, lower dumbbell over and beyond head until upper arms are in-line with torso. Pull dumbbell up and over chest. Repeat.

1446.name: Incline Bench Press
1446.description: Press dumbbells up with elbows to sides until arms are extended. Lower weight to sides of upper chest until slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulder. Repeat.

1447.name: Incline Fly
1447.description: Lower dumbbells outward to sides of shoulders. Keep elbows fixed in slightly bent position. When a stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, bring dumbbells back together in hugging motion above upper chest until dumbbells are nearly together. Repeat.

1448.name: Incline Shoulder Raise
1448.description: Raise shoulders toward dumbbells as high as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

1449.name: Dumbbell Curl
1449.description:
Stand up straight with a dumbbell in each hand at arm's length.
Raise one dumbbell and twist your forearm until it is vertical and your palm faces the shoulder.
Lower to original position and repeat with opposite arm

1450.name: Hammer Curl
1450.description:
Hold the dumbbells with a neutral grip (thumbs facing the ceiling).
Slowly lift the dumbbell up to chest height
Return to starting position and repeat.

1451.name: Hammer Curl
1451.description: With elbows to sides, raise one dumbbell until forearm is vertical and thumb faces shoulder. Lower to original position and repeat with alternative arm.

1452.name: Wrist Curl
1452.description: Allow dumbbell to roll out of palm down to fingers. Raise dumbbell back up by gripping and pointing knuckles up as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

1453.name: Ulnar Deviation
1453.description: Bend wrist so weighted side is pulled upward. Lower until weighted side is pointing downward. Repeat.

1454.name: Radial Deviation
1454.description: Bend wrist so weighted side is pulled upward. Lower until weighted side is pointing downward. Repeat.

1455.name: Reverse Wrist Curl
1455.description: Raise dummbell by pointing knuckles upward as high as possible. Return until knuckles are pointing downward as far as possible. Repeat.

1456.name: Lying Pronation
1456.description: Rotate dumbbell so thumb turns downward (pronation). Return and repeat.

1457.name: Arm Down
1457.description: Rotate dumbbell so thumb turns upward (pronation). Return and repeat.

1458.name: Seated Pronation
1458.description: Rotate dumbbell so thumb turns downward (pronation). Return and repeat.

1459.name: Lying Supination
1459.description: Rotate dumbbell so thumb turns upward (supination). Return and repeat.

1460.name: Arm Down
1460.description: Rotate dumbbell so thumb turns downward (supinated). Return and repeat.

1461.name: Seated Supination
1461.description: Rotate dumbbell so thumb turns upward (supination). Return and repeat.

1462.name: Goblet Squat
1462.description:
Hold the weight tucked into your upper chest area, keeping your elbows in. Your feet should be slightly wider than shoulder width.
Sink down into the squat, keeping your elbows inside the track of your knees.
Push through your heels while keeping your chest up and return to starting position.

1463.name: Dumbbell Row
1463.description:
Place your right leg on the top end of the bench so that your knee and shin rest flat on the bench, your foot hanging off the end.
Bend your torso towards the floor and support yourself with your right arm by placing your palm flat against the bench.
Grip the weight with your left and, and pull it straight up to the side of your chest. Repeat the motion.
Switch the supporting leg and arm to work the other side.

1464.name: Seated Triceps Extensions
1464.description:
Sit on the bench and hold a dumbbell with both hands. Raise the dumbbell overhead at arms length, holding the weight up with the palms of your hands.
Keep your elbows in while you lower the weight behind your head, your upper arms stationary.
Raise the weight back to starting position.

1465.name: Dumbbell Row
1465.description:
Place your right leg on the top end of the bench so that your knee and shin rest flat on the bench, your foot hanging off the end.
Bend your torso towards the floor and support yourself with your right arm by placing your palm flat against the bench.
Grip the weight with your left and, and pull it straight up to the side of your chest. Repeat the motion.
Switch the supporting leg and arm to work the other side.

1466.name: Kickback
1466.description: Extend arm until it is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1467.name: Lying Triceps Extension
1467.description: Lower dumbbells by bending elbow until they are to sides of head. Extend arm. Repeat.

1468.name: Decline Triceps Extension
1468.description: Lower dumbbells by bending elbow until they are to sides of head; dumbbells touch shoulder. Extend arm. Repeat.

1469.name: Incline Triceps Extension
1469.description: Lower dumbbells by bending elbow until they are to sides of head. Extend arm and repeat.

1470.name: One Arm Triceps Extension
1470.description: Lower dumbbell behind neck or shoulder while maintaining upper arm's vertical position throughout exercise. Extend arm until straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1471.name: Overhead Triceps Extension
1471.description: Extend arm until straight while maintaining upper arm's vertical position throughout exercise. Return until dumbbell is behind neck or shoulder and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1472.name: Reclined
1472.description: Lower dumbbell behind neck or shoulder while maintaining upper arm's vertical position throughout exercise. Extend arm until straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1473.name: Triceps Extension
1473.description: With elbows over head, lower forearm behind upper arm by flexing elbows. Flex wrists at bottom to avoid hitting dumbbell on back of neck. Raise dumbbell over head by extending elbows while hyperextending wrists. Return and repeat.

1474.name: Reclined
1474.description: Lower dumbbells behind each side of neck by flexing elbows allowing forearms to travel behind upper arms with elbows remaining overhead. Raise dumbbells overhead by extending elbows until arms are positioned straight and vertical. Lower and repeat.

1475.name: Curl
1475.description: With elbows to sides, raise one dumbbell and rotate forearm until forearm is vertical and palm faces shoulder. Lower to original position and repeat with opposite arm. Continue to alternate between sides.

1476.name: Seated
1476.description: With elbows back to sides, raise one dumbbell and rotate forearm until forearm is vertical and palm faces shoulder. Lower to original position and repeat with opposite arm. Continue to alternate between sides.

1477.name: Incline Curl
1477.description: With elbows back to sides, raise one dumbbell and rotate forearm until forearm is vertical and palm faces shoulder. Lower to original position and repeat with opposite arm. Continue to alternate between sides.

1478.name: Concentration Curl
1478.description: Raise dumbbell to front of shoulder. Lower dumbbell until arm is fully extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1479.name: Preacher Curl
1479.description: Lower dumbbell until arm is fully extended. Raise dumbbell until forearm is vertical. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1480.name: Standing
1480.description: Lower dumbbell until arm is fully extended. Raise dumbbell until forearm is vertical. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1481.name: on incline bench
1481.description: Lower dumbbell until arm is fully extended. Raise dumbbell until forearm is vertical. Repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1482.name: Prone Incline Curl
1482.description: Raise dumbbells until arms are flexed. Lower dumbbells until arms are fully extended. Repeat.

1483.name: Bent-over Row
1483.description: Pull dumbbell to up to side until it makes contact with ribs or until upper arm is just beyond horizontal. Return until arm is extended and shoulder is stretched downward. Repeat and continue with opposite arm.

1484.name: Lying Row
1484.description: Pull dumbbells to sides until upper arm is just beyond horizontal or height of back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

1485.name: Incline
1485.description: Pull dumbbells to sides until upper arm is just beyond height of back. Return until arms are extended and shoulders are stretched downward. Repeat.

1486.name: Shrug
1486.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

1487.name: Lying Shoulder External Rotation
1487.description: Lift dumbbell by rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Flip over and continue with opposite arm.

1488.name: Incline
1488.description: Lift dumbbell upright above elbow by rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Flip body over and continue with opposite arm.

1489.name: Prone External Rotation
1489.description: Lift dumbbell forward and upward by externally rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Grasp with opposite hand, position bent arm out to side of body, and perform with other arm.

1490.name: Incline
1490.description: Lift dumbbell forward and upward by externally rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Grasp with opposite hand, position bent arm out to side of body, and perform with other arm.

1491.name: Seated Shoulder External Rotation
1491.description: Lower dumbbell downward toward lower leg by rotating shoulder until slight stretch is felt. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1492.name: Upright Shoulder External Rotation
1492.description: Lower dumbbell forward by rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1493.name: with Support
1493.description: Lower dumbbell forward by rotating shoulder. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1494.name: on bench
1494.description: Maintaining 90° bend in elbow, lower dumbbell away from body until slight stretch is felt in shoulder. Lift dumbbell toward body by internally rotating shoulder until forearm is across belly. Continue with opposite arm.

1495.name: on floor
1495.description: Maintaining 90° bend in elbow, lower dumbbell toward floor until slight stretch is felt in shoulder. Lift dumbbell toward body by internally rotating shoulder until forearm is vertical and repeat. Continue with opposite arm.

1496.name: Push Crunch
1496.description: Flex waist to raise upper torso from bench, keeping low back on bench. Return until back of shoulders contact padded incline bench. Repeat.

1497.name: Push Sit-up
1497.description: Raise torso from bench as high as possible by bending waist and hips. Keep weight positioned above shoulders. Achieve near upright posture (hip flexibility, incline, and initial hip position permitting). Return to original lying posture with back of shoulders, contacting padded incline board. Repeat.

1498.name: 45° Side Bend
1498.description: Raise torso upward by lateral flexing waist. Lower torso by bending waist downward. Repeat. Position body facing opposite side and continue with opposite side.

1499.name: Russian Twist (on ball)
1499.description: Turn torso to one side while keeping arms straight and perpendicular to torso throughout movement. Return dumbbell back over shoulders by rotating torso to original position. Continue lowering dumbbell to opposite side. Repeat.

1500.name: Side Bend
1500.description: Bend waist to opposite side of dumbbell until slight stretch is felt. Lower to opposite side, same distance and repeat. Continue with opposite side.

1501.name: One Arm Straight Leg Deadlift
1501.description: With knees straight, lower dumbbell between feet by bending hips and twisting waist, so shoulder of weighted side is turned forward. Allow hips to fall back and waist to bend as dumbbell approaches floor. Lift dumbbell upward and back to side by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulder back if rounded. Repeat. Perform exercise with opposite arm.

1502.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
1502.description: With knees straight, lower dumbbells to top or sides of feet by bending hips. Allow hips to fall back and bend waist as dumbbell approaches feet. Lift dumbbells by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back if rounded. Repeat.

1503.name: One Arm
1503.description: With knees straight, lower dumbbell between feet by bending hips and twisting waist, so shoulder of weighted side is turned forward. Allow hips to fall back and waist to bend as dumbbell approaches floor. Lift dumbbell upward and back to side by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulder back if rounded. Repeat. Perform exercise with opposite arm.

1504.name: Lunge
1504.description: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

1505.name: Alternating Side Lunge
1505.description: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

1506.name: Rear Lunge
1506.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

1507.name: Side Lunge
1507.description: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

1508.name: Walking Lunge
1508.description: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

1509.name: Single Leg Stiff Leg Deadlift
1509.description: Lower dumbells to floor while raising lifted leg back behind. Keep back straight and knee of supporting leg slightly bend. Keep hip and knee of lifted leg extended throughout movement. Once stretch is felt or dumbells contacts floor, return to original position by raising torso while lowering lifted leg. Straighten knee of supporting leg as torso becomes upright. Repeat.

1510.name: Single Leg Split Squat
1510.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1511.name: Single Leg Squat
1511.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep   supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1512.name: Split Squat
1512.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1513.name: Squat
1513.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1514.name: Front Squat
1514.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1515.name: Step-up
1515.description: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg, alternating first steps between legs.

1516.name: Lateral
1516.description: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side and forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg alternating between legs.

1517.name: Step Down
1517.description: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

1518.name: Lying Hip Abduction
1518.description: Raise weighted leg up off ground as high as possible, keeping dumbbell positioned on side of upper thigh. Return to leg to floor and repeat. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1519.name: Lunge
1519.description: Lunge forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

1520.name: Alternating Side Lunge
1520.description: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

1521.name: Rear Lunge
1521.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

1522.name: Side Lunge
1522.description: Lunge to one side with first leg. Position closest dumbbell behind thigh and opposite dumbbell to front. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of lead leg, keeping knee pointed same direction of foot. Return to original standing position by forcibly extending hip and knee of lead leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite leg.

1523.name: Walking Lunge
1523.description: Step forward with first leg. Land on heel, then forefoot. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Stand on forward leg with assistance of rear leg. Lunge forward with opposite leg. Repeat by alternating lunge with opposite legs.

1524.name: Single Leg Split Squat
1524.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1525.name: Single Leg Squat
1525.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep   supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1526.name: Split Squat
1526.description: Squat down by flexing knee and hip of front leg. Allow heel of rear foot to rise up while knee of rear leg bends slightly until it almost makes contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1527.name: Squat
1527.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1528.name: Front Squat
1528.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1529.name: Step-up
1529.description: Place foot of first leg on bench. Stand on bench by extending hip and knee of first leg and place foot of second leg on bench. Step down with second leg by flexing hip and knee of first leg. Return to original standing position by placing foot of first leg to floor. Repeat first step with opposite leg alternating first steps between legs.

1530.name: Lateral
1530.description: Lift leg and place foot on bench to side slightly forward of straight knee. Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning feet to original position. Repeat with opposite leg alternating between legs.

1531.name: Step Down
1531.description: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

1532.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
1532.description: With knees straight, lower dumbbells to top or sides of feet by bending hips. Bend waist as bar approaches feet. Lift dumbbells by extending hips and waist until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

1533.name: Straight-back
1533.description: With knees straight, lower dumbbells by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Lift dumbbells by extending hips until straight. Pull shoulders back slightly at top of lift if rounded. Repeat.

1534.name: Standing Calf Raise
1534.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1535.name: Single Leg
1535.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible. Lower heel by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1536.name: Reverse Calf Raise
1536.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1537.name: Single Leg
1537.description: Pull forefoot up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending foot until toes are pointed downward. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1538.name: Shoulder Press
1538.description: Press handles upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

1539.name: Parallel Grip
1539.description: Press handles upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower and repeat.

1540.name: Standing Triceps Dip
1540.description: Push levers down by straightening arms downward. Allow lever bar to raise with elbows pointing back until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Repeat.

1541.name: Gripless Shrug
1541.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

1542.name: Standing Chest Dip
1542.description: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

1543.name: Horizontal Grip
1543.description: Push lever down by straightening arms. Return lever up with elbows flaring out until chest is slightly stretched. Repeat.

1544.name: Leg Hip Raise (Ab Coaster)
1544.description: Slide forward and up by pulling knees up high. Deliberately attempt to flex waist in a "C" shape. Return sled down and back arching spine in opposite direction while keeping hips bent. Repeat.

1545.name: Side Leg Hip Raise (Ab Coaster)
1545.description: Slide forward and up by pulling knees up high. Deliberately attempt to flex waist in a "C" shape. Return sled down and back arching spine in opposite direction while keeping hips bent. Repeat. Turn seat to opposite side and repeat.

1546.name: 45° Leg Press
1546.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1547.name: Alternating
1547.description: Lower one platform toward body by bending knee and hip until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Push platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

1548.name: Single Leg
1548.description: Lower sled by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1549.name: Hack Press
1549.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1550.name: Lying Leg Press
1550.description: Extend hips and knees. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

1551.name: plate loaded
1551.description: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1552.name: Single Leg
1552.description: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1553.name: Single Leg
1553.description: Push platform by extending knee and hip until knee is straight. Return by bending hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1554.name: Seated Leg Press
1554.description: Extend knees and hips until knees are fully extended. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

1555.name: Vertical Leg Press
1555.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1556.name: Single Leg
1556.description: Lower sled by flexing leg until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Push weight up by extending knee and hip. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1557.name: Kneeling
1557.description: Push foot bar up by extending leg   back as far as possible. Return leg to original position and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1558.name: Standing
1558.description: Push platform back by extending leg   back until straight. Return leg to original position. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1559.name: Rear Lunge
1559.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

1560.name: Squat
1560.description: If hand or lever lock is available, disengage weight, squat to lowest position and re-engage lock. Lift sled by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Lower sled by bending knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

1561.name: Hack Squat
1561.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until hips are completely flexed. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1562.name: Single Leg
1562.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knee of supporting leg until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hips. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1563.name: 45° Leg Press
1563.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1564.name: Alternating
1564.description: Lower one platform toward body by bending knee and hip until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Push platform away by extending knee and hip. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating between sides.

1565.name: Single Leg
1565.description: Lower sled by bending leg until knee is just short of complete flexion. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1566.name: Hack Press
1566.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until either is near complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1567.name: Lying Leg Press
1567.description: Extend hips and knees. Flex hips and knees to descend until knees are just short of complete flexion. Repeat.

1568.name: plate loaded
1568.description: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or until hips are completely flexed. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1569.name: Single Leg
1569.description: Bring sled toward platform by flexing hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Return by extending knee and hip. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1570.name: Single Leg
1570.description: Push platform by extending knee and hip until knee is straight. Return by bending hip and knee of supporting leg until knee is just short of complete flexion or until hip is completely flexed. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1571.name: Seated Leg Press
1571.description: Push platform away by extending knees and hips. Return until hips are completely flexed. Repeat.

1572.name: Vertical Leg Press
1572.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Return by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1573.name: Single Leg
1573.description: Lower sled by flexing leg until knees are just short of complete flexion or just before hips raise up from pad. Push weight up by extending knee and hip. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1574.name: Squat
1574.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Raise sled by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1575.name: Hack Squat
1575.description: To lower sled, bend hips and knees until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knees and hips. Repeat.

1576.name: Single Leg
1576.description: Lower sled by flexing hips and knee of supporting leg until knees are just short of complete flexion. Raise sled by extending knee and hips. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1577.name: Rear Lunge
1577.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

1578.name: 45° Calf Press
1578.description: Push sled by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1579.name: Alternating
1579.description: Push sled by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1580.name: Single Leg
1580.description: Push sled by extending ankle as far as possible. Return by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat.

1581.name: 45° Calf Raise
1581.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1582.name: plate loaded
1582.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1583.name: Donkey Calf Raise
1583.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1584.name: Hack Calf Press
1584.description: Push sled up away from platform by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1585.name: Lying Calf Press
1585.description: Push sled away from platform by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1586.name: plate loaded
1586.description: Push sled away from platform by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1587.name: Seated Calf Press
1587.description: Push sled by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1588.name: on lying leg press
1588.description: Push sled by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1589.name: Standing Calf Raise
1589.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1590.name: Forward Angled
1590.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1591.name: Vertical Calf Press
1591.description: Push sled by extending ankles as far as possible. Return by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1592.name: 45° Reverse Calf Press
1592.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1593.name: Single Leg
1593.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heel. Return foot down to platform and repeat.

1594.name: 45° Reverse Calf Raise
1594.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up and back toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed away from body. Repeat.

1595.name: plate loaded
1595.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up and back toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed away from body. Repeat.

1596.name: on hack press
1596.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up and back toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet return to platform. Repeat.

1597.name: Donkey Reverse Calf Raise
1597.description: Pull forefoot up and toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed away from body. Repeat.

1598.name: Hack Reverse Calf Raise
1598.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed away from body. Repeat.

1599.name: Lying Reverse Calf Press
1599.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1600.name: plate loaded
1600.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1601.name: Standing Reverse Calf Raise
1601.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1602.name: plate loaded
1602.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1603.name: Seated Reverse Calf Press
1603.description: Pull forefoot back toward body as far as possible while pushing platform with heels. Return feet down to platform and repeat.

1604.name: Behind Neck Press
1604.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar behind neck and repeat.

1605.name: Shoulder Press
1605.description: Press bar upward until arms are extended overhead. Lower bar to front of shoulders and repeat.

1606.name: Upright Row
1606.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

1607.name: Wide Grip
1607.description: Pull bar to neck with elbows leading. Allow wrists to flex as bar rises. Lower and repeat.

1608.name: Rear Delt Row
1608.description: Keeping upper arm perpendicular to torso, pull bar up toward upper chest until upper arms are just beyond parallel to floor. Return and repeat.

1609.name: Close Grip Bench Press
1609.description: Lower weight to chest with elbows close to body. Push bar back up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1610.name: Incline
1610.description: Lower weight to chest with elbows close to body. Push bar back up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1612.name: Shrug
1612.description: Elevate shoulders as high as possible. Lower and repeat.

1613.name: Bench Press
1613.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

1614.name: Decline Bench Press
