1614.description: Lower weight to chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

1615.name: Incline Bench Press
1615.description: Lower weight to upper chest. Press bar until arms are extended. Repeat.

1616.name: Incline Shoulder Raise
1616.description: Raise shoulders toward bar as high as possible. Lower shoulders to bench and repeat.

1617.name: Bent Knee Good-morning
1617.description: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

1618.name: Deadlift
1618.description: Squat down to lower bar by bending hips and knees. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

1619.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
1619.description: With knees slightly bent, Lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. Keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. Lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

1620.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
1620.description: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as bar approaches top of feet. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

1621.name: Bent Knee Good-morning
1621.description: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Bend knees slightly during descent. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

1622.name: Deadlift
1622.description: Return weight toward floor by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Pull shoulders back at top of lift if rounded. Return and repeat.

1623.name: Stiff-leg Deadlift
1623.description: With knees slightly bent, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. Keep waist straight, flexing only slightly at bottom. Lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

1624.name: Straight-back
1624.description: With knees bent, lower bar toward top feet by bending hips and keeping waist straight. Lift bar by extending at hips until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Extend knees at top if desired. Repeat.

1625.name: Rear Lunge
1625.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs, alternating between sides.

1626.name: Single Leg Split Squat
1626.description: Lower body by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1627.name: Split Squat
1627.description: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1628.name: Squat
1628.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1629.name: Single Leg Squat
1629.description: Bend knee slightly forward while allowing hips to bend, keeping back straight and knee pointed same direction of foot. Descend until thigh of supporting leg is just past parallel to floor. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat.

1630.name: Front Squat
1630.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward   , keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1631.name: Hack Squat
1631.description: Squat down by bending knees forward while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are too close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Repeat.

1632.name: Wide Squat
1632.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward slightly, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1633.name: Rear Lunge
1633.description: Step back with one leg while bending supporting leg. Plant forefoot far back on floor. Lower body by flexing knee and hip of supporting leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward supporting leg and return rear leg next to supporting leg. Repeat movement with opposite legs alternating between sides.

1634.name: Single Leg Split Squat
1634.description: Lower body on leg by flexing knee and hip of front leg until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original standing position by extending hip and knee of forward leg. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1635.name: Split Squat
1635.description: Lower body on other leg by flexing knees and hips of both legs until knee of rear leg is almost in contact with floor. Return to original straddled position by extending hips and knees of both legs. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1636.name: Squat
1636.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1637.name: Single Leg
1637.description: Bend knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thigh of supporting leg is just past parallel to floor. Extend knee and hip until leg is straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1638.name: Front Squat
1638.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet.   Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1639.name: Hack Squat
1639.description: Squat down by bending knees forward slightly while allowing hips to bend back behind, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are too close to parallel to floor and bar is behind lower leg. Lift bar by extending hips and knees to full extension. Repeat.

1640.name: Wide Squat
1640.description: Squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Extend knees and hips until legs are straight. Return and repeat.

1641.name: Step Down
1641.description: Raise bar upward by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Lower body downward by returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

1642.name: Good-morning
1642.description: Bend hips to lower torso forward until parallel to floor. Raise torso until hips are extended. Repeat.

1643.name: Straight-leg Deadlift
1643.description: With knees straight, lower bar toward top of feet by bending hips. After hips can no longer flex, bend waist as bar approaches top of feet. Lift bar by extending waist and hip until standing upright. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

1644.name: Straight-back
1644.description: With knees and back straight, lower bar by bending hips until hamstrings are tight, or just before lower back bends. Lift bar by extending hips until straight. Pull shoulders back slightly if rounded. Repeat.

1645.name: Donkey Calf Raise
1645.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1646.name: Standing Calf Raise
1646.description: Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Repeat.

1647.name: Seated Calf Raise
1647.description: Lower heels by bending ankles until calves are stretched. Raise heels by extending ankles as high as possible. Repeat.

1648.name: Reverse Calf Raise
1648.description: Pull forefoot of both feet up toward body as far as possible. Return by extending feet until toes are pointed downward. Repeat.

1649.name: Triceps Dip
1649.description: Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1650.name: kneeling
1650.description: Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1651.name: Chest Dip
1651.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1652.name: kneeling
1652.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1653.name: Chest Dip
1653.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1654.name: Triceps Dip
1654.description: Lower body until slight stretch is felt in shoulders. Push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1655.name: Chin-up
1655.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1656.name: Neutral Grip
1656.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1657.name: Pull-up
1657.description: Pull body up until chin is above bar. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1658.name: Neutral Grip
1658.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1659.name: Open Centered
1659.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1660.name: Parallel Grip
1660.description: Pull body up until elbow are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1661.name: Rear Pull-up
1661.description: Pull body up until bar touches back of neck. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1662.name: Chest Dip
1662.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight. Repeat.

1663.name: Hamstring Raise
1663.description: Lower body until horizontal by straightening knees. Raise body by flexing knees only allowing hips to bend slightly. Repeat.

1664.name: Triceps Dip
1664.description: Lower body by bending arms back. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees to bend, keeping toes in contact with bench or elevation. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders push body up until arms are straight. Repeat with minimal assistance from legs.

1665.name: Chin-up
1665.description: Lower body under bar until arms and shoulders are fully extended. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees and hips to bend, keeping flat on floor. Pull body up until elbows are to sides, again with minimal assistance from lower body. Repeat.

1666.name: Pull-up
1666.description: Lower body under bar until arms and shoulders are fully extended. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees and hips to bend, keeping flat on floor. Pull body up until chin is just above bar, again with minimal assistance from legs. Repeat.

1667.name: Rear Pull-up
1667.description: Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent allowing knees to bend. Pull body up until bar touches back of neck, again with minimal assistance from lower body. Repeat.

1668.name: Chest Dip
1668.description: Lower body by bending arms, allowing elbows to flare out to sides. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees and hips to bend, keeping forefeet in contact with bench or elevation. When slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, push body up until arms are straight and repeat, again with minimal assistance from legs.

1669.name: Single Leg Squat (bar)
1669.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1670.name: reclining on pole
1670.description: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. With arms slightly flexed, lean back slightly while only allowing knee to travel slightly forward. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Descend to lowest position. Raise body back up to original position while keeping knee behind bar and arms slightly flexed until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1671.name: Single Leg Squat (leg wrapped)
1671.description: Squat down by bending knee forward and hip back behind. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Descend until thigh is just past parallel to floor. Return to standing position with minimal assistance from wrapped leg. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1672.name: Squat
1672.description: While holding onto horizontal bar, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

1673.name: on suspension trainer
1673.description: While holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

1674.name: Step Down
1674.description: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

1675.name: Single Leg Squat (bar)
1675.description: Squat down as far as possible while keeping leg elevated off of floor. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Raise body back up to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1676.name: reclining on pole
1676.description: Squat down while keeping leg elevated off of floor. With arms slightly flexed, lean back slightly while only allowing knee to travel forward slightly. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as supporting foot. Descend to lowest position. Raise body back up to original position while keeping knee behind bar and arms slightly flexed until knee and hip of supporting leg is straight. Repeat and continue with opposite leg.

1677.name: Single Leg Squat (leg wrapped)
1677.description: Squat down by bending knee forward and hip back behind. Keep back straight and supporting knee pointed same direction as foot supporting. Descend until thigh is just past parallel to floor. Return to standing position with minimal assistance from wrapped leg. Stand to original position until knee and hip of supporting leg are straight. Return and repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1678.name: Squat
1678.description: While holding onto horizontal bar, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

1679.name: on suspension trainer
1679.description: While holding onto suspension trainer handles, squat down by bending hips back while allowing knees to bend forward, keeping back straight and knees pointed same direction as feet. Descend until thighs are just past parallel to floor. Stand up by extending knees and hips until legs are straight. Return to standing position and repeat.

1680.name: Step Down
1680.description: Stand on bench by straightening leg and pushing body upward. Step down returning foot off of bench to floor and repeat. Continue with opposite position.

1681.name: Inverse Leg Curl
1681.description: Lower body with hips straight by slowly straightening knees. Position hands forward, ready to push body weight back up off of surface. Control descent only with hamstrings as low as possible before catching body by quickly placing hands on elevated platform and rapidly pushing off against platform, just enough to assist hamstrings in raising body upward. Return to upright kneeling position and repeat.

1682.name: on floor
1682.description: Lower body with hips straight by slowly straightening knees. Control descent only with hamstrings as low as possible. Only when body begins to fall, touch down with tensed finger tips out to each side. Once fingers make contact with floor, control remaining descent with assistance of arms. Allowing chest to come very close to floor, rapidly push off against floor, again just enough to assist hamstrings in raising body upward. Return to upright kneeling position and repeat.

1683.name: Single Leg Calf Raise
1683.description: Raise heel by extending ankle as high as possible, assisting with upper body as little as possible. Lower heel by bending ankle until calf is stretched. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1684.name: with other leg
1684.description: Raise body upward as high as possible by extending lower ankle while straightening knee of assisting leg. Lower heel by bending ankle while bending knee of assisting leg forward. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg positioning.

1685.name: One Hand Grip
1685.description: Squeeze bar grips together until far bar makes contact with nearest bar. Release to original position and repeat.

1686.name: Grip (plate loaded)
1686.description: Squeeze bar grips together until lower bar makes contact with upper bar. Release to original position and repeat.

1687.name: One Hand
1687.description: Squeeze bar grips together until lower bar makes contact with upper bar. Release to original position and repeat.

1688.name: One Hand Pinch Grip
1688.description: Pinch surfaces together until lower part makes contact with upper part. Release to original position or just before surfaces become too far apart. Repeat.

1689.name: Chin-up
1689.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1690.name: Parallel Close Grip Pull-up
1690.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1691.name: standing
1691.description: Pull body up until elbow are to sides. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1692.name: Pull-up
1692.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1693.name: open centered-bar
1693.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1694.name: standing
1694.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1695.name: Chin-up
1695.description: Pull body up until elbows are to sides or chin is just above bar. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1696.name: Pull-up
1696.description: Pull body up until chin is just above bar. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1697.name: Rear Pull-up
1697.description: Pull body up until bar touches back of neck. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1698.name: Pull-up
1698.description: Pull body up until neck reaches height of hands. Lower body until arms and shoulders are fully extended. Repeat.

1699.name: Self-assisted
1699.description: Lower body under handles until arms and shoulders are fully extended. If necessary, use minimal assistance of lower body to control descent, allowing knees and hips to bend, keeping flat on floor. Pull body up until chin is just above handles, again with minimal assistance from legs. Repeat.

1700.name: Clap Push-up
1700.description: Lower body to floor and immediately push body up as fast as possible. As the hands leave ground, rapidly clap hands together and place back to original position, catching body before it falls. Repeat.

1701.name: Depth Push-up
1701.description: Lower body to floor and immediately push body up as fast as possible. As hands leave ground, rapidly place hands on platforms to sides, catching body before it falls. Lower body again. As soon as slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, immediately push upper body upward. Before upper body falls, immediately remove hands off of platforms and catch body by returning hands back on floor between platforms and repeat.

1702.name: Clap Push-up
1702.description: Lower body to floor and immediately push body up as fast as possible. As the hands leave ground, rapidly clap hands together and place back to original position, catching body before it falls. Repeat.

1703.name: Depth Push-up
1703.description: Lower body to floor and immediately push body up as fast as possible. As hands leave ground, rapidly place hands on platforms to sides, catching body before it falls. Lower body again. As soon as slight stretch is felt in chest or shoulders, immediately push upper body upward. Before upper body falls, immediately remove hands off of platforms and catch body by returning hands back on floor between platforms and repeat.

1704.name: Medicine Ball Sit-up
1704.description: First participant lies back with ball over head and taps ball to floor. First participant immediately throws ball to partner from over head while sitting up. Partner catches ball slightly above and in front of head and repeats steps. Participant and parter continue to volley ball back and forth.

1705.name: Broomstick Twist
1705.description: Rotate torso through waist to one side, then to the opposite side. Repeat.

1706.name: Seated
1706.description: Both individuals rotate torso through waist to same side. First partner hands medicine ball to second partner who retrieves ball. Both individuals turn to the opposite side to again exchange medicine ball. Continue to rotate ball to one direction. When finished, repeat opposite direction.

1707.name: apparatus
1707.description: Rotate torso through waist to highest side of ball ramp. Place medicine ball on ramp. Release ball and turn to opposite side. Grasp ball as it travels to other side. Continue to transfer ball to highest side of ball ramp and catch it on opposite side. When finished, adjust ramp to opposite incline and repeat movement in opposite direction.

1708.name: Standing
1708.description: Both individuals rotate to opposite sides. First partner hands medicine ball from behind to second partner who retrieves ball from behind. Both individuals turn to the opposite sides to again exchange medicine ball from behind. Continue to rotate ball in a figure 8 one direction. When finished, repeat opposite direction.

1709.name: apparatus
1709.description: Rotate body to highest side of ball ramp. Place medicine ball on ramp. Release ball and turn to opposite side. Grasp ball as it travels to other side. Continue to transfer ball to highest side of ball ramp and catch it on opposite side. When finished, adjust ramp to opposite incline and repeat movement in opposite direction.

1710.name: Knee Hug
1710.description: Pull knee toward body until stretch is felt in hip. Release and step forward with stretched leg. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating stretch and step between each leg until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

1711.name: Walking Ankle Grab
1711.description: Pull foot and lower leg upward until stretch is felt in hip. Release and step forward with stretched leg. Repeat with opposite leg. Continue by alternating stretch and step between each leg until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

1712.name: Walking Quadriceps Stretch
1712.description: Standing on left foot, position right foot behind and grasp it with right hand. Pull right heel toward right glute while pulling right knee down and back. Release right foot, step forward with right foot, and repeat on left side while standing on right foot. Continue by alternating between each side until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

1713.name: Soldier Kick
1713.description: Next step, extend left arm forward while swinging right leg up so foot touches or comes close to hand. Lower right leg. Repeat with same sequence on opposite side. Continue by alternating between each side until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

1714.name: intermittent
1714.description: Next step, extend left arm forward while swinging right leg up so foot touches or comes close to hand. Lower right leg, then take two steps, with left and right legs. Repeat with same sequence on opposite side. Continue by alternating between each side followed by double steps until specific distance is covered or desired number of repetitions have been completed.

1715.name: Hip Flexion
1715.description: Raise lever by flexing hip until knee is higher than hip. Return until hip is extended. Repeat. Continue with opposite leg.

1716.name: Lying Leg Raise
1716.description: Raise legs by flexing hips until they are completely flexed. Lower legs until hips are extended. Repeat.

1717.name: Vertical Leg Raise
1717.description: With back straight, raise legs as high as possible by flexing hips. Return and repeat.
